title: hummus
directions: In blender (in batches) or in food processor, process chickpeas, tahini and lemon juice until mixture reaches consistency of coarse paste; use as much of reserved pea liquid or water as needed.
Add garlic, coriander, cumin, paprika and cayenne and process again.
Transfer to a bowl and add scallions. Cover and chill one hour before serving the dip.
Add parsley as garnish.

title: american apple pie
directions: Clean and slice apples. Add all ingredients.
Put in prepared pie crust.
Brush top of pie with cream.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain off grease.
Add soups. Rinse cans out well.
Add the macaroni.
Mix well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until macaroni is tender.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Pour cherries and juice in saucepan.
Heat to a boil, then add sugar and jello.
Stir until sugar and jello are dissolved; remove from heat.
Chill partially and add pineapple and nuts.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Wash squash thoroughly; cut into slices. Cook in small amount of water until tender. Drain well and mash. Measure enough to make 2 cups. Combine squash, eggs and margarine.
Stir well and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl. Make well in center of mixture. Add squash mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: dough ornaments
directions: Knead bread for 10 minutes.
Don't let ornaments or dough dry out.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Put wire in before baking.
You can roll dough out or form shapes in your hand.
Bake in foil-lined cookie sheet for 2 hours at 300°.
Baste with milk to make them brown.
You can shellac them and then use acrylics to paint them.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix together the milk and pudding.
Add butter mixture and pudding mixture together and add the Cool Whip.

Layer in a bowl the Oreo cookies, 1/2 pudding mix, then layer Oreo cookies and rest of pudding mix and rest of Oreos. (thick layer last) Refrigerate overnight. Serve with gummy worms on top, along with flowers, serve with garden trowel.

title: santa fe chili
directions: Brown beef in shortening in heavy skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and beat in eggs.
Stir in pineapple and bread crumbs.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pineapple nut upside-down muffins
directions: Combine
brown
sugar
and
margarine.
Portion
scant teaspoon into
each
of
12 greased 2 1/2 inch muffin pan cups. Place pecan
half in each.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and
sugar; set aside.
Measure 40% Bran Flakes, pineapple and milk
into large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Let stand about 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil;
beat well.
Stir in chopped pecans. Add
flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
(Batter will be thick.)
Portion
evenly into muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° about 25
minutes or until browned.
Invert into serving plate. Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: ants on a log
directions: Clean and chop celery into 4-inch pieces.
Spread peanut butter on celery.
Put raisins on top.

title: spicy mix
directions: Combine all and store in airtight container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat the cream cheese (room temperature) until fluffy.
Slowly add soup and other ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove 1/2 hour before serving.

title: oven easy meatballs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with 1/3 cup Manwich.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Pour remaining Manwich, mixed with water over meatballs.
Cook 15 minutes, turning and basting often. Makes 6 servings.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Cut lettuce into pieces; dice tomatoes.
Slice onion.
Slice cucumber and mix them into one large bowl.
Open tuna fish and mix with the other ingredients in the bowl.
Pour half a bottle of salad dressing and mix.
Add black pepper and salt to taste.
Put in a refrigerator for 5 to 10 minutes and serve.

title: euna's sweet potato casserole(very good!)
directions: Combine potatoes, beaten egg, sugar, margarine, milk and spices.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: spicy cornbread muffins
directions: Combine first 4 in bowl.
Make a well in center.
Combine eggs and next 3 items.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened. Spoon into muffin pans that have been coated with cooking spray. Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
There are 115 calories per muffin.

title: mom's quick praline cookies(makes 48 cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay crackers end to end in large jelly roll baking pan (24 should fill a standard pan, it must have sides).
Cook butter and sugar over medium-high heat, stirring constantly until it comes to boil.
Reduce to low heat and simmer for 2 minutes and add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spread over crackers. Bake for 10 minutes.
Spread into squares while warm and lift onto cooling rack with narrow spatula.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk, and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour and spoon into unbaked pie crust.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: popcorn cake
directions: You will need a Bundt pan (buttered).

title: cheers from beth!
directions: Combine equal parts of both beverages for a great pick-me-up!

title: aunt clarice cloyd henson's chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, sugar, salt and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add 1/2 cup cooked mix to yolks. Mix well and return yolk mix to double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute green pepper in 1/4 cup of butter or margarine.
Add 1/4 cup flour, milk, salt, sugar and dash of pepper.
When thickened, add cheese, tomatoes, corn and lima beans, broccoli and drained onions.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt; add oats.
Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture.
In a heavy saucepan melt together milk, chocolate chips, margarine and salt.
Stir until smooth; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pat 2/3 oat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spread chocolate mixture over dough.
Dot with remaining oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coffee gelatin
directions: Stir together and pour 2 cups boiling water over mixture. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla. Refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours).

title: meat loaf
directions: Spread over top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings. Delicious for sandwiches.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until incorporated.
Whisk together sweet potatoes and 3/4 cup milk in small bowl until blended.
Gradually stir into flour mixture until blended.
Do not over-mix.
If dry, add remaining milk, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Dough should stick together.
Place dough on floured surface.
Knead 8 - 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick. Cut out 2 inch biscuits.
Bake at 425 degrees for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 20 biscuits.

title: aunt eliza's pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add one egg at a time to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla to milk.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add half to mixture with half of the milk; blend well.
Add rest of flour mixture and milk; mix well.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Test center for doneness with toothpick.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; do not overcook.
Peel, slice and salt potatoes as you layer them.
Fry bacon.
Add flour, then vinegar, sugar, water, salt, onion and butter.
Boil until thickened.
Pour over potato slices.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine milk, egg, salt and mustard.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to milk and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Dip wieners into batter and fry in deep fat.
Makes about 9 corn dogs.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Boil until tender the lasagne noodles (about 10 minutes). Prepare filling by mixing tofu that has been mashed, Parmesan, 3 egg whites and spinach that has been steamed and drained very well.
Add spaghetti sauce to mixture except 1/2 cup.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, pineapple, pepper, onion, salt and half of the nuts and shape into a ball.
Roll ball in remaining nuts.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press roll dough onto a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, dressing, dill seed and garlic salt. Mix until well blended and spread on cool crust.
Top with vegetables.
May use any other kind of vegetable your family likes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: surprise pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk, pineapple and lemon rind.
Last mix in lemon juice (it makes it all stick together).
Place in crust and chill for 1 hour.
Top with toasted coconut and serve.

title: microwave party mix
directions: Combine cereals, nuts and pretzels in a 4-quart bowl. Microwave butter and seasonings in a separate bowl until butter is melted.
Pour over cereal mixture and toss until all mix is evenly coated.
Microwave cereal for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir several times during cooking.
Stores well in an airtight container.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti noodles.
Mix eggs, milk, 1 c. mozzarella cheese, garlic
and a dash or two of salt.
Spread into a greased pan and bake 15 minutes at 400°. When done, layer spaghetti sauce, remaining cheese, then whatever pizza toppings you want.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set for 5 minutes. Enjoy!

title: curry-triscuit appetizers
directions: Mix spread a day ahead and refrigerate.
Put spread on Triscuits (do not use any other cracker!).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately!

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, blending 8 minutes.
Pour half of batter into tube type cake pan.
Spread 1/2 broken Hershey bar on top.
Pour in remaining batter.
Top with remaining 1/2 Hershey bar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting.

title: frozen cheese sandwiches
directions: Cut crust from bread.
Beat butter until very soft.
Add Old English cheese.
Mix well.
Add onion powder, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, dill seed, Beau Monde powder and cayenne or red pepper.
Using 3 slices of bread per sandwich, spread mixture on each layer and on top, not on sides.
Cut in 4 squares.
Freeze immediately.
Bake frozen 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pickle chips
directions: Heat 1 inch of oil in a heavy skillet or electric skillet to 375°.
Combine egg and pickle liquid.
Combine bread crumbs and garlic salt.
Coat each pickle slice with flour; dip in egg/pickle mixture.
Fry in small batches 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until browned, turning once.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Dissolve soda in boiling water. Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: white trash
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Pour over Crispix cereal.
Add the pretzels and nuts; mix well.
Put confectioners sugar in large bag.
Pour all ingredients into bag; shake or mix well.
Put in freezer.
Break apart and serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: "422" hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove stems and ends.
Cut in rings.
Sprinkle salt over peppers.
Let stand overnight.
Mix well so all the salt is dissolved.
Drain overnight in large colander (with peppers in a plastic bag with a lot of holes punched in the bottom).

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine pudding and milk; beat with electric mixer until well blended, about 3 minutes.
Gradually blend in chocolate until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip topping.
Turn into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a rolling boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add Certo, stirring in all at once.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add green food coloring.
Fill small jars and cap with 1/8-inch wax.
Cool overnight, then cover. Makes 7 or 8 baby food jars.

title: strawberry-pineapple delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: 1-2-3 flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Caramelize 1 cup sugar in a saucepan over medium heat until brown and melted.
Pour into a Bundt pan. Swirl pan to coat sides and bottom.
Let set until cool.

title: granny william's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix cream of tartar, flour, salt and baking soda.
In another bowl, mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, then add flour mixture slowly on low.
Chill mixture about 2 hours or until you can make balls about walnut size.
Make balls and roll them in the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place them about 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheddar crust apple pie
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
Add water while mixing lightly with a fork; form into ball.
Divide dough in half.
On lightly floured surface, roll dough ball to 12-inch circle.
Place in 9-inch pie plate.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes. Place in a pot with enough water to cover them. Salt to taste and boil until done. While the potatoes are cooking, put the eggs on to boil. When potatoes are done, drain the water off and place in a large bowl; peel the eggs and add them and the mayonnaise to the potatoes. Mix well.

title: crunchy munchy muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In small bowl, beat eggs, orange peel and juice, honey and oil until well blended.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in carrots, nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into baking cups, filling to top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: vanilla pudding dinner rolls
directions: Cook pudding as directed, adding margarine as the pudding cooks.
Cool.
Mix yeast with warm water and add sugar.
Mix pudding and yeast mixture together.
Beat in eggs and salt.
Add flour, mixing well.
Knead lightly.
Put into greased bowl.
Cover with towel and let rise for 2 hours.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and form into rolls.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening.
Mix with a fork.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Roll out dough very thin on floured board.
Use floured cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: strawberry cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, tear apart the cake and layer the bottom of pan.
Make sure bottom of pan is covered.
Next layer, pour over strawberries (they need to be thawed out).
Tear apart remaining cake and cover strawberries.
Mix up vanilla pudding and pour over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
This is better if made the day you want it.
It can be made the day before and frozen, take out of freezer about 3 hours before serving.
You can use cherry pie filling instead of strawberries.

title: creamed corn
directions: Add all and cook 4 hours in crock-pot on low.
Stir occasionally after oleo starts to melt.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over meat in pan.
Let set in refrigerator overnight (or at least 8 hours).
Remove from refrigerator one hour before cooking.
Drain marinade from meat; save.
Broil meat 10 minutes on each side.
Heat marinade in pan and pour over meat after it is cooked.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add molasses, milk and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields approximately 3 dozen.

title: fresh tomato soup
directions: Wash and cut up tomatoes.
Chop onions, celery, parsley and bay leaves.
Add to tomatoes and cook until celery is tender.
Put through a sieve.
Rub flour and butter into a smooth paste, thinned with some tomato juice.
Add to the boiling soup and stir to prevent scorching.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Fill jars and put on sterilized caps and seal.
Process in water bath 15 minutes. Carrots and zucchini may be added if desired.
(Two teaspoons vinegar should be added to each jar if processing by water bath.)

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat vigorously 1/2 minute with spoon. Fill 12 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat above with mixer.
Add 1/2 cup sweet milk to mixture. Pour into unbaked pie crust.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Cut potato in half.
Peel, dice and boil until tender; drain. (Only use a piece of potato about the size of an egg.)
Mash potato with fork; add vanilla and slowly add confectioners sugar, mixing well by hand.
Keep adding sugar until have a stiff dough.
Roll out on wax paper sprinkled with confectioners sugar in a rectangular oval.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into a log and slice.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings in listed ingredients (which have been mixed in blender) for about 2 hours.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours, turning and basting with marinade.
Crisp in broiler briefly, if desired.

title: company rice pilaf
directions: Brown vermicelli in a large saucepan in the melting butter, stirring constantly.
Stir rice into butter.
Add boiling water to rice and cook for 20 minutes on low to medium until water is gone.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Heat
oil
and	water
in
small saucepan until bubbly. Turn off
heat;	stir
in flour with tablespoon.
Work toward center of pot to form a ball.
Put in pie pan and pat out with hands.
Press up sides of pan.
Precook for custard pie.
Can also be rolled between wax paper.

title: chocolate nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: shrimp and broccoli
directions: In pan, on medium heat, cook broccoli in olive oil with garlic powder until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Add shrimp and lemon juice.
Cook 5minutes, stirring often.
Serve over noodles or rice.
tags: Ramen Pride chicken flavor ramen noodle soup mix

title: carolina she crab soup
directions: Heat butter; add onions and celery.
Simmer.
Add flour, stir and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add half and half and 1 cup cream. Boil slowly for 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg and mustard to taste.
Add remaining cup of cream and crab meat.
Simmer several minutes.
Before serving, add sherry; heat thoroughly. Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Put in crock-pot on low for 4 hours or bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Heat 1/4 cup grapefruit juice.
Do not boil.
Dissolve marshmallows in juice.
Put a few in at a time and stir constantly. Remove from heat after marshmallows are all dissolved.
Stir in grapefruit pulp.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours before serving.
Can top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: beverly's pineapple-cheese casserole
directions: Add pineapple and 3 tablespoons pineapple juice.
In bowl mix everything, except margarine and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased pie pan or dish.

title: "acini de pepe salad"(pasta fruit salad)
directions: Drain fruits (pineapple and oranges) from their juice, but save pineapple juice.
Cook sugar, flour, eggs and pineapple juice until thick; set aside and cool.
Cook acini de pepe (macaroni).
Drain and cool.
Mix with the cooked mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day, add fruits and miniature marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in a skillet; add onions.
Let brown; add remaining ingredients, one at a time; simmer slowly, about 10 minutes.
Pour in a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mango bread
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add mango and lime juice, then add flour, soda, pecans, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: cherries jubilee(serves 8)
directions: Drain cherries; add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add juice.
Cook over direct heat until slightly thickened.
Add cherries.
Heat.
Remove from heat and place in heatproof bowl or dish.
Add liquor.
Ignite with match, bring to table and spoon over ice cream.

title: rosemary's potato casserole
directions: Partially thaw potatoes.
Saute onion in melted butter or margarine.
Add thawed potatoes, cheese, soup and sour cream. Mix well and put in large casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Cook in a 350° oven for at least 45 minutes.
Crush a few potato chips and sprinkle on top.
Cook about 20 minutes more until browned and potatoes are done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Heat the olive oil in a deep skillet.
Add onion and bay leaves and saute over medium heat until the onion is soft (5 to 8 minutes).
Add eggplant, peppers, mushrooms, salt and basil. Cover and cook until the eggplant is tender (10 to 15 minutes), stirring occasionally.
Add wine, tomatoes and black pepper. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes uncovered (the liquid will reduce).
Stir in the garlic during the last 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook the pasta.
Drain the pasta; toss with a little additional olive oil and ladle the eggplant on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and parsley and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
In a 2-quart oblong baking dish shape into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: great chili
directions: Brown onions and then ground beef in the oil. Add flour and mix well. Mash 1/2 cans of kidney beans (in electric mixer) while browning onions and beef. Add tomatoes, all of kidney beans and seasonings. Simmer 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Cook in large pot. Freezes well.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix with electric mixer.
Pour in partially baked pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: marinated beef
directions: Brown roast, then marinate in mixture overnight.
Cook in marinade until tender.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch casserole dish with whole graham crackers. Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add and bring to a boil the egg, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Remove from heat and add the next 3 ingredients.
Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.
Top with frosting.
Refrigerate before cutting into small servings.
Keeps well in refrigerator for weeks if tightly covered.
Freezes well, also.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: orange fluffy salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle jello.
Stir to mix well.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Mix together; chill at least one hour before serving.

title: susan's ever famous and delicious chinese chicken salad
directions: Take shredded lettuce and line a large platter.
Bake the chicken breasts with soy sauce and cool.
Shred chicken and marinate.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Mash well with fork.
Add remaining ingredients except ham and mix well.
Put a tablespoon of mixture on each slice of ham and spread evenly.
Roll ham lengthwise and place folded side down on cookie sheet; cover with Saran Wrap and freeze for 45 minutes.
Remove and slice each roll into 9 to 10 pieces.
Makes about 3 dozen.
They may be stored in freezer up to 6 weeks.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Dredge the beef with the seasoned flour, patting off the excess.
Melt half the butter in a large, heavy based casserole or pan over a medium heat and when foaming, brown the meat on all sides, turning it with wooden spoons or a spatula.
When well browned, add the onion stuck with the cloves, bay leaf and thyme and pour on the stock.
Cover the pan, reduce the heat to low and cook on top of the stove or in a preheated 300° oven.
Cook slowly for about 2 hours, adding more liquid, either stock or water, as necessary.
Test the meat and, if beginning to feel tender, add the vegetables.
Cover and continue to cook until the meat is completely tender and the vegetables are cooked through.
Remove the meat and vegetables from the casserole or pan and place them on a warm serving platter.
Skim the excess fat from the top of the sauce and bring it back to the boil.
Mix the remaining butter and the all-purpose flour to a smooth paste.
Add about 1 teaspoon of the mixture to the boiling sauce and beat thoroughly with a whisk. Continue adding the mixture until the sauce is of the desired thickness.
Carve the meat and spoon over some of the sauce.
Serve the rest of the sauce separately.

title: date-nut-filled cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch around layer pans.
Prepare, bake and cool cake as directed.
For filling and frosting, put dates, water, butter and sugar into a heavy saucepan.
Cook stirring constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens (about 8 minutes).
Remove from heat and add pecans.
Cool.
Spread between cooled layers and on sides, top of cake.
Chill.

title: cranberry orange glazed cornish hens
directions: Rinse hens, pat dry.
Coat inside and outside of hens with melted butter, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place hens, breast side up, on a rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer.
Cover loosely with foil.
Roast in 375 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and roast one hour or until thermometer reads 185 degrees.
Meanwhile, for sauce, in a one quart saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, orange marmalade, lemon juice, minced onion and corn starch.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in orange sections.
Brush sauce on hens several times during last 20 minutes of roasting.

title: ring-a-ding beans
directions: Cook ground beef until it loses redness. Drain excess fat. Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with cheese for the last 10 minutes of baking time. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mini cheese blintzes
directions: In food processor, mix cream cheese, egg yolk, vanilla and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Flatten bread with rolling pin and spread with cream cheese mixture.
Roll up.
Melt butter.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon in dish.
Roll bread in butter and then in the sugar mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Slice each roll into 3 pieces and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm with sour cream for dipping.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple annie's banana banshee
directions: Blend the whole banana, creme de cacao, cream of banana, ice cream and ice in a blender for 30 seconds.
Garnish with a banana slice.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In large saucepan bring broth to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat to low.
Add macaroni, celery flakes and oregano. Simmer 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add stewed tomatoes, green beans, chickpeas and garlic powder.
Simmer 5 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: rosemary linguini(heart healthy)
directions: Cook linguini in boiling water.
Drain.
Toss with olive oil, Parmesan cheese, rosemary, basil, pepper spice, onion, garlic, parsley, artichoke hearts, olives and tomatoes until well mixed. Serve hot immediately.

title: oven fried chicken breast(very low fat)
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Lightly salt and pepper (to taste). Dip each piece in yogurt.
Dredge in crumbs.
Lightly spray a cooking sheet with Pam.
Place chicken on cooking sheet and lightly spray each piece of chicken with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, turning once to ensure even cooking.

title: delicious vegetable pot roast
directions: Take large knife; make four deep slits in roast.
Cut four pieces of pepperoni and push into slits.
Cut slits in roast and put slices of garlic into slits.
Season meat with Mrs. Dash, pepper, A.1. sauce, teriyaki barbecue marinade sauce.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Heat oil in roasting pot.
Brown roast on all sides.
Cover 1/2 of roast with water.
Add onions.
Cook on low for 1 hour.
Cook on high for 1/2 hour.
Add soup mix and frozen vegetables.
Continue cooking for another 1/2 hour.
Remove meat; drain juice from vegetables.
Make gravy with juice.
Serve meat with vegetables and gravy over rice.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot and simmer until vegetables are done or you can cook all day.

title: strawberry bavarian cake
directions: Combine all in a large bowl.
Pour in tube pan and refrigerate overnight.
Ice with Cool Whip.

title: salmon spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salmon, in a small bowl. Blend well with a fork.
Drain salmon, crumble and add to mayonnaise mixture.
Blend well.
Chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Add softened yeast. Add remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead, then place in bowl and cover.
Let rise until double, then punch down and let rise again.
Divide dough in half and roll each in a rectangle.
Brush lightly with melted butter, then sprinkle with the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Tightly roll dough as for jelly roll. Place in greased loaf pan.
Let rise, then bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, pepper, sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs and add to squash.
Add by tablespoon.
Cook on both sides until delicate brown.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Melt oleo in dish; add 1/2 of dressing mix.
Add chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Cover with remainder of dressing mix.
Add 2 cups of chicken broth over all.
Bake about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: creamy corn soup
directions: In saucepan, heat soup, milk, mayonnaise and corn (with liquid), stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 5 servings.

title: michigan chili
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and place in a large heavy pot. Chop onions and add to bacon.
Cook together until onions are soft, but not brown.
Add beef and brown meat.
Drain off fat and return meat to pot.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 2 hours or more, adding water when needed and stirring occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: choc-o-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, spices, all dry ingredients and sugar. Beat eggs until foamy. Add pumpkin, oil and cereal to eggs and mix.
Beat in dry ingredients. Stir in chips and nuts. Spread in ungreased tube pan or Bundt pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water, deboned.
Cook spaghetti
in chicken broth.
Do not drain.
Cut up cheese; add to spaghetti. Cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender; add to spaghetti with Ro-Tel, chicken and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake on low for 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Put on cookie sheet to set.
We made this at school. Good.

title: cherry surprise(egg nog)
directions: Drop cherry in tall glass.
Put rest of ingredients in mixing bowl.
Whip with blender 30 to 60 seconds or until frothy.
Pour in glass with cherry.
Add a straw.
Makes 1 serving.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Put drained pineapple chunks in bottom of cake pan.
Mix cake mix as directed; pour over pineapple.
Bake as directed.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Boil the noodles until tender.
While the noodles are cooking, cook the ground beef, onion and green pepper until the beef is brown.
Add both sauces and mushrooms to the beef; simmer for 10 minutes.
Next, begin layering ingredients in a crock-pot.
First, add a layer of hamburger mixture, then a layer of both cheeses. Start all over with meat mixture and continue layering until all ingredients are used.
End with the cheese on top.
Cook in crock-pot on high until cheese is melted, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange curried chicken
directions: Remove skin and all visible fat from chicken breasts.
Place in baking dish.
Combine orange juice, lemon juice, curry and salt. Pour over chicken and cover.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired, and serve with brown rice.

title: mike's mexican eggrolls
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add the next 7 ingredients.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Uncover; cook an additional 5 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
Set aside.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Boil until able to pierce easily with fork.
Hollow out seeds and set aside.
Cut potatoes into small cubes, about size of croutons.
Cook in pan sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
(Small amounts of water may need to be added during cooking.)
Cook sausage; mash and drain off fat.

title: grandma ruths's goulash
directions: These amounts are approximate to when we had 3 small children. The last time I made it, I used three 3 1/2 pound sirloin roasts.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Mix 2 Tbsp. cinnamon and 4 Tbsp. sugar and set aside.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Pour one-half of batter into pans.
Sprinkle the cinnamon and sugar mixture over the batter and then spread the rest of the batter on top of the cinnamon and sugar mixture. Twirl a knife through batter to make it marble.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chop pretzels and layer over melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Blend sugar and cream cheese; spread over hot pretzels.
Spread Cool Whip over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate.
Boil pineapple juice and dissolve Jell-O in juice.
Add strawberries until thawed. Refrigerate until soft like jelly.
Spoon over Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set, about 4 hours.

title: cassie's spaghetti
directions: After browning and draining ground chuck, add spaghetti sauce. Also add oregano, a dash of garlic powder and salt.
In a separate pot, prepare spaghetti noodles according to package directions. Drain spaghetti and add sauce.
Let simmer slowly for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and a "little" of the water.
Mix until smooth.
Beat egg yolks; add to sugar mixture.
Stir well. Add remaining water.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Cover; cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon rind, juice, salt and butter or oleo.
Mix well.
Pour while hot into (chilled) pie crust.
Whip egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Swirl on pie.
Bake in moderately low oven at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: onion dressing
directions: Mix well and add in very slowly 1 cup oil.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender and can be picked off the bone. Save the broth that the chicken was cooked in.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Add Veg-All vegetables.
Pour vegetables over the chicken.
Then add chicken soup mixed with chicken broth (saved from chicken).
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and butter.
Pour over chicken mixture and bake at 375° until brown.
Season to taste.

title: jo-nell's fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill about 30 minutes.
Keeps well.
Make ahead.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box, except use pienapple juice instead of water.
Add coconut, nuts and pineapple and bake in 3 layers.
Save some pineapple, nuts and coconut for top of cake.

title: glazed raisin loaf
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Add hot milk; stir to dissolve sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of the flour; mix well.
Add yeast and eggs; beat well.
Stir in remaining flour, mixing well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes).
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover; let double (1 1/2 to 2 hours) in warm place.
Punch down; cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Shape in loaf.
Place in greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover; let almost double (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 25 minutes.
Place foil over top last 10 minutes if necessary.
Remove from pan; cool.
Glaze with confectioners sugar icing.

title: chicken piccata(serves 2 as scaled; original recipe serves 2)
directions: Blend flour, thyme and pepper.
Flatten chicken with mallet or plate (place between waxed paper).
Dredge chicken in flour.
Add olive oil to preheated heavy saute pan and quickly brown chicken over medium-high heat, about 2 minutes per side.
Remove and set aside.
Saute onion until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add chicken, wine and lemon juice and cook until sauce thickens, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: ice cream and cookies dessert
directions: In large bowl, crush cookies.
Spread 2/3 cookies into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and chocolate in microwave.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, sugar and nuts.
Add chocolate mixture; beat well.
Pour mixture over cookies.
Spread ice cream evenly over sauce.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Freeze 2 hours before serving.

title: baked apples
directions: Wash the apples, but do not peel them.
Cut off the tops and remove the cores.
Place close together in an ovenproof casserole dish.
Combine the nuts, raisins and cinnamon; fill each apple with this mixture.
Place a teaspoon of honey on top of each filled apple and top with a bit of margarine.
Pour the juice around the apples in the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, basting after the first 15 minutes of baking.

title: homemade bread
directions: Combine
oats,	boiling
water,
oleo and milk in large bowl. Let
stand	20
minutes for quick oats, nearly one hour for regular.
Dissolve	yeast in warm water.
Add to oats when cool. Add
other	ingredients
except
flour.
Stir in 4 cups flour and beat
strokes.	Add
more
flour until workable dough is obtained.
Grease
hand and bowl with lard and knead until springy and
smooth.
Let	set
in bowl until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Punch down again.
Put in well greased pans.
Let	rise
again.
Bake
for 50 minutes or
until done.
Makes 5 or 6 loaves.
You could make 1/2 recipe if you don't want so much.
But with a large family this doesn't last long.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Put brown sugar and water on stove and boil until it spins a thread, then add the syrup slowly to well beaten egg whites.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Spread on cake and cover with chopped nuts if desired.

title: greek cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lasagna specialty
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add spices, water, tomato paste, tomatoes, egg and mushrooms.
Cook 20 minutes.
Fold in cottage cheese. Make in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan: 1 layer of 4 noodles, 1 layer of 1/2 sauce, 1 layer with half of cheese mixed together. Repeat with second layer.
Bake in a 350° oven until all cheese melts and starts to turn golden color, approximately 20 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Arrange cabbage and onions in layers and top with sugar. Bring vinegar, oil, 2 Tbsp sugar, mustard, celery seeds and salt to a boil and pour over cabbage and onions.

title: cranberry crunch a la mode
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the rolled oats, flour, brown sugar and butter with a pastry blender until crumbly.
Spread half of this mixture evenly to cover bottom of the pan.
Spread the cranberry sauce evenly over the crumbs. Cover the top with the rest of the crumbs.
Bake the dessert 25 minutes.
Serve it hot, cut into bars, with a scoop of vanilla ice cream on top.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sugar, spices and salt in bowl.
Stir in milk and butter.
Add pumpkin.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool and garnish with whipped cream.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Mix guacamole dip.
Layer 7 ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crumb pies
directions: Mix
flour
and
sugar together.
Now cut in oleo.
Set aside. Mix molasses and hot water which soda and vinegar have been added to.
First,
put
half of liquid in pie shell (unbaked), then crumbs on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cook noodles until partly done.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Saute onion and ground pepper; brown the ground meat. Combine all ingredients and pour over the noodles.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Place cooked potatoes in greased baking dish.
Melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk.
Cook and stir constantly until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until blended.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated catfish fillets
directions: Marinate fillets for 2 to 3 hours in mustard, canned milk, salt and pepper mixture.
Roll fillets in cornmeal.
Fry to light golden brown in 1 inch of grease in hot skillet.
Catfish fries fast, so don't overcook.
It should be crispy on outside and moist on the inside.
Don't knock it if you haven't tried it.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese spreads together with mixer. Add cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Mix all together. Refrigerate until it sets a little. Roll in finely chopped nuts. Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in sugar, raisins, milk, vanilla, salt and hot rice.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake uncovered 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally, until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold and, if desired, with cream.
Refrigerate any remaining pudding.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese softened, then mix together all ingredients except pecans and form into ball or log.
Then roll in pecans until well covered.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: grandma travis's homemade macaroni
directions: 1. Cook macaroni. Place in casserole dish, add seasoning, cheese, beaten eggs, and hot milk together.
2. Pour over noodles & stir. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Trim the ends from the stems of the mushrooms.
Wash them quickly; dry immediately and cut each mushroom in half.
Mix salt, pepper, oregano, wine vinegar and oil together.
Add the mushrooms and toss until all the pieces are well coated.
Let stand at room temperature for 4 hours.
Serve with picks as a cocktail accompaniment or as a relish.

title: chocolate chewy(the icing is baked right on the cake.)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with shortening or margarine on bottom and sides of pan. Combine pudding mix and milk in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring to prevent sticking on bottom. Stir dry cake mix into pudding. Pour into greased cake pan and sprinkle nuts and chocolate chip morsels over top of batter. Place pan in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut in squares and serve. Great warm!

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, vinegar, water and oleo.
Cook to 235°.
Add baking soda and stir.
Pour over popped corn.
Shape into 3-inch balls.

title: carrot oat muffins
directions: Combine oats and buttermilk in a mixing bowl and let stand 15 minutes.
Beat egg with honey.
Meanwhile, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir with egg into the oat mixture.
Fold in carrots and orange rind, stirring only enough to moisten all ingredients.
Spoon into muffin cups sprayed with low-fat cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: jewel salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Then dissolve in boiling water, stirring in sugar and salt.
Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and vinegar; let cool.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg whites; then add the drained cucumber and pineapple.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs and press into oblong pan.

title: picante dip
directions: Blend all together until smooth.
Chill before serving.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix oil, eggs, Bisquick and spices.
Next, mix in zucchini and cheese.
Place in 2 greased pie pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown on top.

title: rocky road
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, extending foil over the edges of pan.
Butter foil; set aside.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix oil, eggs, sugar, nuts, apples, vanilla and orange juice.
Combine with dry ingredients. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Form into balls.
Place in casserole.
Mix together soup and milk or water for sauce. Pour over balls.
Cover; bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dianne daughtrey reed's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli until almost done.
Blend eggs, mushroom soup and onion and cook until a sauce is formed.
Then add the cheese and
mayonnaise
to
the
sauce.
Place
broccoli
in a baking dish
and
cover with the sauce.
Top with bread crumbs and bake in a moderate (350°) oven until bubbly.

title: rice-apricot-marshmallow pudding
directions: Soak washed apricots overnight in enough water to cover.
Cook slowly in same water until tender.
Drain.
Add honey and sugar to taste.
Arrange a layer of hot rice, then apricots in a greased dish; sprinkle with a layer of marshmallows cut in quarters.
Let brown in oven.
Add second layer of rice, apricots and juice with marshmallows on top.
Let brown in moderate oven.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: green with envy salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water in mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients by hand.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in one large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions; cool.
Add diced vegetables and Italian dressing.
Toss with Salad Supreme seasoning.
This is best when served at room temperature.

title: broccoli and pasta
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Melt oil and oleo together.
Add garlic and saute.
Do not allow garlic to burn.
Add chopped broccoli to oil and saute 2 minutes.
Add pasta; stir.
Sprinkle in cheese; stir.

title: caramel nut rolls
directions: In a 2-quart casserole or mixing bowl, place caramels, butter and milk.
Microwave at 50% power 3 to 5 minutes or until melted and smooth, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar until smooth and then add peanuts.

title: easy grill top bread
directions: Let onion stand in water 5 minutes, then combine with butter and parsley.
Slash bread on bias, cutting to, but not through, bottom crust.
Spread onion butter on one side of each slice.

title: cream cheese horns
directions: Cream together to form dough.
Divide into 2 balls.
Flatten and refrigerate to chill dough.
Roll into a large rectangular shape on a sugared-floured board.
Cut into squares. Dot with preserves.
Pinch opposite corners to close.
Bake at 400° to 410° for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown.
Remove from oven. Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes two large cookie sheets.
Recipe may be doubled and dough stays in refrigerator a day or so.

title: civil war cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Cook, bringing to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Add apple mixture, stirring to blend only.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: lemon greek salad
directions: Score cucumber by running tines of fork lengthwise down sides; slice.
Toss cucumber slices and remaining ingredients with Lemon and Mustard Dressing.

title: aunt bebe's bean bowl
directions: Mix everything and marinate for 24 hours.
Stir a few times while it marinates.
Drain all dressing off; serve in lettuce lined bowl.

title: green chocolate dessert
directions: Crush the cookies and add the melted butter.
Dissolve the Jell-O in the hot water.
Add the lemon juice and sugar.
Let stand while whipping the Carnation milk. Add Jell-O to milk.
Add the lemon rind and green coloring. Whip until stiff. Butter dish, putting half of cookies in bottom and half on top.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix one package lemon jello with 1 cup hot water.
Set aside to cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips and blend well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve hot.

title: summer squash bake
directions: Cook squash and onion in small amount of boiling, salted water 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
In bowl combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
In large mixing bowl, toss melted butter with stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture atop stuffing.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over top.
Bake at 350° to heat through (about 20 minutes).

title: chocolate cake(two 8-inch layers)
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add fat and half of the milk.
Beat until creamy.
Mix in remaining milk, vanilla and eggs.
Add chocolate and beat until creamy.
Pour into two 8-inch cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.
Frost with creamy chocolate frosting.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil hen in at least 1 1/2 quarts water.
Saute peppers and onions in butter.
Cook vermicelli in broth; leave in.
Add Ro-Tel and 1/2 of the cheese to broth.
Add Worcestershire.
Cook until thick.
Cut up cheese; stir until melted.
Add drained peas and onion mixture.
Remove chicken from bone.
Add salt and pepper. Place in 3-quart casserole.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole (for microwave)
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a 10 x 10 x 1 3/4-inch dish. Lay chicken thighs on top of rice mixture.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Turn back one edge of wrap to allow steam out. Cook with microwave at High for 20 minutes.
Halfway through cooking time, stir rice from corners of the dish.
Remove wrap and continue cooking.
Brush chicken with melted butter and brown.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1- inch baking pan or 13 x 9- inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all bar ingredients; stir until well blended.
Spread in pan. Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
For 15 x 10 x 1- inch pan,
bake 20 - 30 minutes.
For 9 x 13 pan, bake 25 - 30 minutes.
Pour and spread frosting over warm bars.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 48 bars.

title: cheese and bacon potatoes
directions: Place bacon in cold skillet.
If using electric skillet, turn temperature to 325°.
Fry until crisp.
Remove and drain.
Remove grease from skillet, leaving 2 tablespoons in skillet.
Add potatoes to skillet, cover and cook 10 minutes.
Turn potatoes and cook 10 more minutes or until tender.
Crumble bacon and combine with green chilies and onion.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple; set juice aside.
Mix together sugar, egg, cornstarch and pineapple juice; cook until mixture becomes thick. Pour this over the cheese, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix together.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Put in food processor to chop up. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, garlic powder and salt.
Cook over low heat, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.
Set aside.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package.
Need enough for 2 layers.
In a bowl, mix together beaten eggs, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until apples are mushy. Mash!
Makes about 3 cups.
Can be put in sterilized jars.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well and roll out about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Frost with stiff white icing.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cold water.
Chill until thick, but not set.
Stir in cranberry sauce, celery and nuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold or leave in bowl. Serves 8.

title: dill potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When cooled, peel skins off. Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: marinated shrimp canapes
directions: Several Hours Before Serving:
Pour the dressing over the shrimp. Cover and refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate; set aside.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Cream softened cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Beat.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon in pie crust.
Chill four hours or overnight.

title: vienna squares
directions: Pour over crust.
Return to oven and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pop cake
directions: Follow instructions for making cake on cake mix box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and while still hot, poke holes into cake (all over) with fork tines.
Mix Jell-O, boiling water and pop together.
Pour over cake.
Let cool; mix pudding according to instructions on box.
When set up, mix with Cool Whip and use to frost cake.
Store in refrigerator.
You can vary pudding and pop flavors and create your own taste treat.

title: cranberry banana salad
directions: Soften gelatine in water.
Heat cranberry sauce and marshmallows over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Add gelatine and stir.
Chill until partially set.
Add in bananas, lemon juice and red food coloring (optional).
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill until firm.

title: popcorn caramel
directions: Boil all ingredients except soda and popcorn for 6 minutes. Take off heat and add soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix well. Grease pan.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli.
Grease casserole dish.
Put in broccoli.
Chop up cooked chicken and put on top of broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and juice well.
Pour over chicken.
Then add cheese. Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over everything.
Bake at 350° until well heated, approximately 30 minutes.

title: cornbread for chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, pouring melted Crisco in last.
Mix until well blended.
Bake at 450° about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chit-chat
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Bake another 30 or 40 minutes uncovered.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Add the rest of ingredients to the hamburger mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar and 2 tablespoons cream.
Cook over boiling water until sugar is dissolved.
Cut up both kinds of chocolate.
Remove double boiler from heat, but leave top over bottom.
Add chocolate to cream mixture, stirring until melted.
With spoon, beat in remaining cream.
Serve warm. Makes 1 cup.

title: meatball appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients (to taste) in crock-pot and heat.

title: wild fruit salad
directions: Mix together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: hootenanny cake
directions: Grease the bottom of a tube pan.
In a larger bowl, mix the ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.

title: pasta "perfect" salad
directions: Cook spiral noodles according to package. Drain thoroughly. Mix all ingredients.
Pour dressing over mixture to marinate.
Do not over use.
Chill so flavor can reach full potential.
Enjoy with everything!

title: green pea salad
directions: Layer salad ingredients in order listed, beginning with lettuce.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. In a large bowl combine all the
above ingredients and mix well.
Pat into a 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole.

If desired, spread the top with additional catsup. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until the meat is to your liking. To be sure that the meat loaf is done, I usually cut into it near the middle and take a peek.

title: willye's molasses cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Add spices, salt and soda to flour.
Mix into creamy mixture.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll out into balls the size of walnuts. Dip tops in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place sugar side up on a greased cookie sheet 3-inches apart. Bake at 300° until soft, not hard.

title: ritz pineapple dessert
directions: Mix crackers, baking powder and nut pieces together and set aside. In separate bowl, beat egg whites, sugar and vanilla. Fold cracker mixture into egg whites, sugar mix. Bake in 9 x 13 greased pan at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli.
Mix together with cheese and soup. Put in dish and crumble crackers over top with a few slices of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: bohemian cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add vanilla. Sift flour and measure 1 1/4 cups and sift with salt three times. Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Using a meat grinder, grind nuts and chocolate together; fold into creamed mixture. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 250° oven for 40 minutes.

title: popcorn
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine and 14 large marshmallows.
Place in microwave oven for 4 minutes.
Stir until melted.
Add large bag popcorn and pour syrup over popcorn.
Place on cookie sheet and place in oven.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°; stir often while in oven (every 15 minutes).
Cool on wax paper.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Slice potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out about 3/4 of flesh and set aside for other use.
Set skins on cookie sheet and place in oven about 4-inches away from top element.
Broil for 8 minutes.
Remove skins from oven and sprinkle with both cheeses. Season well and add bacon and paprika.
Broil another 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot with sour cream.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage in pan. Slice cheese and add to meat. Stir until cheese melts. Add a dash of oregano. Put meat mixture on plain white bread; put in oven on broil until bread browns.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemonade and condensed milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill until firm.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix in large bowl, popped corn, candies and coconut.
Melt 1 stick oleo and 1 pound marshmallows.
Pour over first ingredients. Stir and mix together. Pack firmly in Bundt pan or other mold. One package jello can be added for flavor and color.

title: mushroom and mozzarella hamburgers
directions: Mix ground beef and onions and make patties; cook your favorite way at your desired doneness.

title: tuna cutlets
directions: Drain tuna well.
Lightly mash the potatoes, leaving small lumps.
Mix in the lemon juice, cilantro, green onions, green chilies, onion, salt, red pepper flakes, and garam masala.
Now add the tuna and mix well.

title: corned beef congealed salad
directions: Heat jello, water, bouillon cube and Worcestershire sauce. Cool.
Add corned beef, onion, eggs, celery and mayonnaise.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass casserole ring mold or individual molds.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all together except potato chips. Place in a 9 x 13 greased pan. Refrigerate overnight. Just before baking, sprinkle crushed chips on top of mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla flavoring.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: In a plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients and shake. Empty into a shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: unreal mayonnaise-quickie
directions: *For improved flavor, use 1/4 cup soyagen powder and 1/4 cup almond powder.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash
avocados and blend in rest of ingredients.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 cups of dip.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate cherry delight
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Chill until partially set.
Stir together all other ingredients.
Layer jello and chocolate mixture into parfait glasses.
Chill until firm.
Has flavor of chocolate covered cherries.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease 10 x 15 jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add milk; mix flour and sugar and add to the egg mixture.
Stir in coconut and flavoring.
Pour into crust and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Ingredients will be layered in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Spread ground beef evenly and not too thick in bottom of baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use dry soup mix, about 1/3 of envelope, and sprinkle over meat.
Next spread mixed vegetables over meat.
Use canned soup of your choice and smooth over vegetables.
Then place Tater Tots (as many as you can) in a single layer on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then turn down to 350° for 30 minutes.
Your Tater Tots may brown quicker if oven is hotter.
May also take longer if ground beef is too thick.
Serve with a salad and bread of your choice and you have a meal.
Serves about 4.
For more, double recipe and use a bigger dish.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Parkay.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon, then add flour.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into cubes 1/2-inch or less.
Lightly brown beef cubes in corn oil or spray (use as little oil as possible).
Add about 1 tablespoon butter (more if you want) and a mixture of 1/2 wine and 1/2 water (leave out wine if you're not into that sort of thing). Salt and pepper to taste.
Use very little salt if using cooking wine!
Add onion.
Cook this mixture over medium heat until beef is tender.
Begin with meat, barely covered with liquid, and allow the liquid to evaporate while cooking.
If more liquid is needed, you may add butter, wine and/or water.
Keep in mind that you want only a little liquid with the meat and onion when done.
Try to avoid the temptation to sample too much of the remaining wine during the cooking process.
Add sour cream to taste.
Do this slowly.
Too much sour cream will overpower the other flavors.
Serve with wide egg noodles.
Serves four.

title: eagle brand mix
directions: Dissolve sugar and butter in boiling water.
Mix all in blender until thick and creamy.
Makes 1 1/4 cups or 1 can.

title: pepsi pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place roast in baking pan (I use a 13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle dry soup over top of canned soup that has been spread over roast.
Pour Pepsi over all.
Cover pan with lid and do not look until 3 1/2 to 4 hours of cooking.
(Also can put carrots around edges before cooking.)
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars, egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into balls by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Place chocolate Kisses into middle of each cookie and press down lightly.
Bake 2 more minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart glass baking dish in microwave.
Stir together flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Stir gently to mix with the butter. Add fruit that has been tossed with remaining sugar.
Don't stir. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: lemon dumplings
directions: Mix
water,
lemon,
sugar
and molasses and bring to a boil. Make
dumplings by mixing remaining ingredients together.
Drop dumpling
mixture
into the simmering liquid.
Cook until dumplings
are
done,
turning
once.
(Small ones take about 3 minutes.) When all dumplings are done, remove from the liquid
and thicken
the
liquid slightly with flour and pour over the dumplings.
Good hot or cold.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown
chops in small amount of
cooking
oil.	Combine two soups and pour
over
chops.
Bake in oven uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve on creamed potatoes or cooked rice.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the cream cheese; add sugar and beat eggs in one at a time.
Add vanilla. Fill cupcake liners 3/4 full.
Bake for about 50 minutes at 325° until light brown.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla and spoon into centers.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: poor man's frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour. Cook until a soft paste-like pudding. Cool completely. Add sugar, oleo and Crisco. Beat for 15 minutes, then add vanilla. Mix well.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan in which margarine has been melted.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add flour, sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Pour over cranberry-nut mixture and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Can be served warm with whipped cream or cold with ice cream.

title: souffle topped herb chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, or place each portion in an individual baking dish.
Sprinkle green onions and tarragon on top.
Dot with butter; season with salt and pepper.
Add wine.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Beat egg white to stiff peaks; fold in mayonnaise.
Spoon mixture on top of chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes more, or until light brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread rice in large baking dish.
Place pieces of chicken on rice.
Add water.
Spread oleo on top.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake for 40 minutes, covered, at 350°.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine vanilla wafers with one stick melted margarine well on bottom of 8 1/2 x 13-inch dish.
Beat together remaining stick of margarine, confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on top of crust.
Add can of drained pineapple on top of cream cheese mixture.
Slice bananas and cover with whipped topping.
Place pecans and cherries on top.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Pour undrained	pineapple
into
a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over this and sprinkle cake mix over top.
Sprinkle
nuts
and	coconut
over
this.
Cut margarine into
thin	patties and arrange on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: white salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff, then add sugar and beat again; add Ritz crackers and mix together.
Press into cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat Dream Whip (as directed on package, but for 2 envelopes) until stiff.
Drain can of pineapple into a bowl (save the juice).
Cream the cream cheese with the juice to make creamy.
Mix all together (Dream Whip, creamy-cream cheese and crushed pineapples), and pour over top cooled Ritz cracker mixture.
Add nuts on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Add all ingredients and mix gently.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Before serving, mix a few times. Great for picnics!

title: bible cake
directions: Follow Solomon's prescriptions Proverbs 23:14 and beat well. Bake at 325° until done.
Makes 2 small cakes or 1 large cake.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat egg; stir in milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Add 2/3 cup crumbs.
Add corn.
Pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter; add rest of crumbs.
Mix; sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan with margarine.
In a small saucepan, combine raisins and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in applesauce.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves and mix into batter.
Add applesauce mixture and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix milk, 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of salt in 1-quart size Ziploc bag.
Expel most of the air and close securely.
Add ice cubes and 6 tablespoons of salt to gallon size Ziploc bag.
Place ice cream mixture in smaller bag inside large bag with ice and salt.
Close securely.
Shake and roll bags several minutes until ice cream is soft frozen.
Eat and enjoy!

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Scoop out potatoes, careful not to tear skin.
Mix all ingredients in bowl. Fill potato skins with mixture. Garnish with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: dad's chocolate gravy
directions: In saucepan, warm milk to almost boiling. Set off heat. Mix together dry ingredients. Add 2 cups warm milk. Mix to get lumps out of mixture. Now, pour back in saucepan. Cook on medium to medium-high heat until thick.

title: my mother's apricot nectar pound cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Beat
well and pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 40
to
45 minutes at 350° or until done.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: soy chicken
directions: Sprinkle soy sauce and garlic powder over chicken in pan for oven.
Marinate 1 hour.
Turn chicken and sprinkle again.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes, skin side down.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more with skin side up.

title: s. o. s.
directions: Brown meat; add oleo and stir.
Add onion and cook until translucent.
Add flour; stir and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add garlic, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce and mix thoroughly. Add milk and stir until it thickens.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for exactly 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: 2 pineapple pies
directions: Carefully separate eggs.
Place whites in deep narrow bowl. Mix flour with sugar.
Cut up butter and add to sugar along with pineapple and egg yolks.
Stir while cooking to thick stage. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool.
Add 1 teaspoon warm water to egg whites.
Beat stiff and add 5 teaspoons sugar.
Pour pineapple mixture in 2 cooked pie shells.
Add egg whites and bake until brown.

title: cheesy onions
directions: Peel onions and quarter.
Make white sauce and pour over grated cheese.
Pour mixture over onions in buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger broccoli casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper, chopped onions and chopped celery in electric skillet.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Mix the soups together and heat.
Put half the browned beef in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Layer half the broccoli, then onion rings, cheese and finally the soup.
Repeat the layers. Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: pie crust(fat-free)
directions: Measure flour into large bowl.
Add oil to flour and mix well until like soft putty.
Add warm water and mix by hand until all water is absorbed.
Roll out between 2 pieces of wax paper that have been lightly floured.
Makes 2 pies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions and Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, powdered sugar, margarine, oil and eggs until smooth.
Add the flour (a little at a time), cream of tartar, baking soda and vanilla; mix well.
Refrigerate dough for 2 hours. Roll out on a flour covered board.
Then you may use your desired cookie cutter to cut cookies.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 7 to 9 minutes at 375°.
Serves 36.

title: "carne con papas"(cuban beef and potato stew)
directions: Saute beef with the olive/cooking oil in a pressure cooker. Once the meat is well cooked, add the ingredients MINUS the potatoes, olives and food coloring. Cover and cook with pressure for 15 minutes. Once the cooker has cooled off completely, add the remaining ingredients. Cook at medium heat until the potatoes are soft and the liquid has thickened. Turn off heat and add 1 teaspoon of Spanish olive oil. Before serving, garnish with Spanish pimentos. Serve with a salad, rice and fried green plantains. Makes 4 servings.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in lard with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse meal. In a separate bowl, mix together the water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture.
This will be enough for two double crust pies or four singles.
Will keep tightly covered in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
This crust will not soak through.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Combine 1/4 cup brown sugar, 2 teaspoons orange juice and 2 teaspoons of butter.
Mix and set aside for glaze topping.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Add other ingredients, mix and refrigerate.

title: sweet bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Melt margarine in milk on low temperature.
(Cool down a little.)
Add in a bowl, eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and yeast.
Add flour.
Batter will be tacky.
Set to raise in a warm spot until double in size. (This may take a few hours.)
Knead dough with flour and make loaves.
Let loaves raise again, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 loaves.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, on low for 1 1/2 hours at least.

title: spicy stuffed mandarins
directions: Wash mandarins, cover with water and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain and cool enough to handle.
Cut off 1/4-inch top of mandarin.
Put half of date in core of each mandarin.
Mix all ingredients and heat to boiling, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Place mandarins in a baking dish.
Pour 1/2 teaspoon of syrup over date and mandarin flesh, replace top.
Cover mandarins with remaining syrup, bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven. Cool mandarins in syrup, drain before serving.
Serves 8.

title: strufulas
directions: Add eggs, one at a time, to flour and salt. Add remaining ingredients. Form dough into small balls and deep fry. Pour honey over cooked Strufulas and cover.

title: one hour turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Put all ingredients in roasting pan. Seal well with foil. Bake for 1 hour.

title: crispy yeast waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, yeast, sugar and salt; mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk and butter or margarine until warm (120° to 130°); butter does not need to melt.
Add to flour mixture; add eggs.
Blend at low speed of mixer until moistened. Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and foil; refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Stir down batter. Bake on waffle iron on medium heat.
Serve hot with butter and toppings.
Makes 6 to 8 large waffles.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread crumbs over butter evenly with fork.
Spread chocolate chips, then spread coconut and pecans together and press with fork.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until slightly brown.

title: disney walnut bread
directions: Mix yeast in warm water and let dissolve.
Combine flour, salt, sugar and walnuts in large mixing bowl.
Add milk, oil, eggs and yeast.
Using bread hook (if you have one), mix at slow speed to blend liquid and dry ingredients.
When blended, return to medium speed for 15 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes. Turn dough out on a lightly floured board and cut 6 equal pieces. With floured hands, knead into loaf shape and place on 2 baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 loaves.

title: squash casserole
directions: Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add butter and Crisco, then beaten eggs and milk. Beat at medium speed. Add vanilla. Bake in large spring-form pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Start in cold oven. Punch holes in your cake and let some of icing soak in before it gets thick (right after taken off stove).

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Mix together rice and soup mix.
Place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
