Put chicken pieces on top of rice mixture. Mix together chicken soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Uncover last half hour.

title: grandma's dutch apple pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in unbaked pie crust.

title: jewish apple cake(all in one bowl)
directions: Place all ingredients, except apples, in mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and put half in tube pan.
Cover with a layer of half of the thinly sliced apples.
Sprinkle apples with sugar-cinnamon to suit your own taste.
Cover with rest of batter.
Arrange remaining apples on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour and 50 minutes, but, you can check your own oven.
Insert toothpick to test for doneness.

title: carrot salad
directions: Place raisins in hot water 10 minutes and drain.
Place in large bowl the carrots, raisins, pineapple, mayonnaise, Equal and juice.
Mix and chill.

title: appetizer spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in Ziploc bag until needed. Bake frozen for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and butter together.
Mold into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolates in double boiler.
Drop chilled balls into chocolate.
After they are coated, chill and eat!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread dinner rolls out on pan.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Take out and pat down rolls.
Bake additional 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: fried apples
directions: Add sliced apples to oleo and brown sugar in frying pan.
Cook until apples are tender.

title: nana's garlic and herb cheese
directions: Process all ingredients in food processor or mince parsley and beat all ingredients in a medium size bowl with electric mixer until blended and smooth.
Pack into 1 pint decorative container or dish.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Delicious with party breads or crackers or use as a tangy topping for steak or hamburgers.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time alternately with 2 cups flour to dredge fruits and nuts. Add lemon extract. Fold in egg whites, fruits and nuts. Let stand overnight in the refrigerator. Put into large angel food pan or 2 loaf pans. Bake slowly 3 hours at 225° or until done. Cool. Wrap well in wax paper or foil and store in airtight container. If cake seems dry to your taste, mix the last 3 ingredients and pour over cake while warm. Serves 12 to 15.

title: louise's chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Mix cranberry sauce, mushroom soup, French salad dressing and onion soup mix together. Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients
and cook to 236° (soft ball stage).
Add nuts and Karo.
Stir until coating on nuts begins
to sugar.
Spread nuts on cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart while coating is still soft.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir constantly over heat until mixture thickens. Let cool and pour over fruit.

title: seafood (crab) bisque
directions: Saute onions.
Combine all ingredients, using seasonings to your taste and put in crock-pot or large pot and heat through. Serve with oyster crackers and tossed salad.
You may want to double the recipe.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add cooked macaroni and cheese (already mixed well) and the can of Manwich.
Let this simmer for about 5 minutes, then put into casserole dish.
Add the cheese to the top and let melt.

title: beef and squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil for 5 minutes in salt; drain and place in a buttered dish.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Put margarine over this.
Brown 1/2 to 1 pound ground beef and add to casserole. Season to taste.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 300°.

title: chili-n-chips
directions: Brown 1 pound ground meat and drain.
Add chili beans and simmer.
Blend together cheese and taco seasoning, cream and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add blended mixture to meat and beans.
Heat all together.
Serve over chips.

title: tomato-cucumber salad
directions: Slice tomatoes, cucumber and onion.
Add salt, oregano and oil; gently toss.
Serve with fresh Italian bread.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Combine in medium saucepan marshmallow creme, sugar, evaporated milk, margarine and salt.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan. Chill in refrigerator until firm (2 hours).

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding together.
Then add oil, milk and eggs.
Beat at least 5 minutes.
Fold in grated German sweet chocolate.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured tube pan.
Pat the semi-sweet morsels over the top of batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 2 qt. casserole dish. Mix all ingredients together and bake uncovered 1 hr.

title: hamburg cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger
and
season to taste.	Chop cabbage in small pieces and cook until tender.
Add tomatoes to hamburger and mix with cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Pour 1 cup raw rice (not Minute) in casserole.
Arrange 10 pieces of chicken on top.
Mix 1 can mushroom soup with 2 cans of water and pour over rice and chicken.
Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix on top.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Add more water if needed.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Stir margarine, sugar and milk in pan.
Bring to full boil; stir constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour on greased pan.

title: quick salad
directions: Note:
Use all one size (small, medium or large).

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, melt butter over low heat. Add the flour; stir with wire whisk until blended.

title: dessert grillers
directions: Spread butter mixture onto sliced pound cake.
Grill on both sides.
Let cool.
Place assorted fruits onto skewers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil thoroughly.
Form into small balls, about 3/4 inch.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Heat oil in frying pan and deep fry meatballs for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: cornucopias
directions: Mash cheese with onion and drained pickle relish.
Spread on a slice of boiled ham.
Roll cornucopia fashion.
Chill.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Rinse pea pods; remove tips and strings.
Cut onion tops in 1-inch lengths and thin slice white portions.
Slice water chestnuts; quickly rinse mushrooms and blot dry.
(Do not slice until ready to cook.)
Arrange all on tray, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: potato donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll 3/4 to 1-inch thick.
Cut into pieces about 1 1/2 x 2-inches.
Deep fry at 375° until brown. Drain on paper towel.
May be rolled in cinnamon and sugar or confectioners sugar while warm.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen small donuts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole with cover, stir together sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; mix well and microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour in lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin and cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut oleo into cake mix (dry) until crumbly. Pat mixture lightly into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks; drizzle over apples.
(Topping will not completely cover apples.)
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
(Do not overbake.)
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Good on all vegetables.

title: mary's crisp waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
In a pitcher, combine egg, corn oil and club soda; mix well.
Stir in Bisquick.
Pour batter into heated waffle iron and cook according to appliance directions.
Makes crisp waffles.

title: tuna french toast sandwich
directions: Make tuna salad with first four ingredients.
Make tuna sandwich with 2 slices of bread.
Beat egg and milk; dip sandwich on both sides.
Fry in pan with butter.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Lay chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Rinse sauerkraut twice with cold water.
Layer it over the chicken. Cover with Thousand Island dressing (moderately generous) to sustain moisture.
Cover these ingredients with Swiss cheese, thinly sliced.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Get ready to prepare the same dish really soon again.

title: jellied salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sour cream and cold water; then add drained pineapple and oranges.
Stir ingredients together and set in a salad mold.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers, onion and green pepper.
Cover and set in refrigerator 1 hour; drain.
Mix vinegar, celery salt or seed and sugar.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Mix well.
Place in covered jars and refrigerate.
Can be kept 2 weeks.
Makes 2 full mayonnaise jars.

title: stuffed franks
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Slit franks lengthwise.
Spread open and fill with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased pan.

title: pumpkin upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In medium bowl, lightly beat eggs. Add remaining filling ingredients; stir until well combined. Pour into ungreased 9 X 13 baking dish.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread mixture in an 8 x 8-inch pan or quiche dish. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cut in wedges and serve warm.

title: peach shake
directions: In a mixing bowl or blender, beat together the chopped peaches, peach syrup (from the canned peaches) and mace.
Add peach ice cream, gradually add milk, beating until all ingredients are blended.
Serve immediately.

title: mike gatton's favorite shish kabobs
directions: Marinate overnight in Worcestershire sauce and teriyaki sauce (marinate 2 cups soy sauce and 1 cup lemon juice for 2 hours). Thread cubes of steak on skewers and alternate mushrooms, pepper strips, tomatoes, onion and potatoes until all is used.
Do same with chicken.
Grill on gas grill until meat is done.

title: sesame chicken breasts
directions: Toast the sesame seed in a medium-size no stick skillet over moderate heat.
Shake the pan frequently until seeds are golden brown.
Transfer to a shallow bowl or pie plate.
Add bread crumbs and mix thoroughly.
Cover with plastic wrap and hold for final preparation.

title: chocolate lust
directions: Make bottom layer first.
Mix flour, butter and pecans together.
Press it in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Chop the chipped beef.
Mix with cream cheese.
Mold into ball. Serve with crackers.

title: magic lemon cream pie
directions: Mix together beaten egg whites and add sugar to meringue.

title: dirty pickles
directions: Mix the water, salt and vinegar; pour over well packed pickles.
Put 2 grape leaves in jar (1 in bottom of jar and 1 in top of jar).
Makes enough for 3 quarts.
Do not wash cucumbers; wash when you open to eat.

title: corny cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg custard no-crust
directions: Grease pie plate with butter and dust with flour.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour in pie plate; bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk, stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and flour; mix well.
Pour into cake pans and bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apricot-banana sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and salt with a small amount of apricot nectar in medium saucepan.
Stir in remaining apricot nectar and honey gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and butter. Add banana slices to sauce.
Serve over waffles, French toast or pancakes.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: sweet sour bean salad
directions: You will need 3 or 4 separate bowls to mix ingredients and your serving dish.

title: monster cookies
directions: Reserve 1/4 pound M&M's for decorating, if desired.
Cream eggs, sugars and butter.
Add peanut butter and cream well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes, 6 cookies to a sheet.
Makes 100 large 4-inch cookies.
I make them smaller and have more cookies.

title: pepper sauce
directions: Wash pepper; pack in a quart jar.
Boil enough vinegar to fill jar.
Pour boiling vinegar over pepper.
Seal with a ring and can flat.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add apples, walnuts and bits. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of muffin pans.
Beat egg with fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Blend in combined dry ingredients, stirring just until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Loosen immediately.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: corn bread
directions: Put oil in pan and a little flour hot. Combine ingredients. Bake at 500° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and mash with a fork on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sugar free oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and beat well. Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 10-15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in bananas and pineapple.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until berries have thawed.
Add nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Place in refrigerator and allow to set.
Spread sour cream evenly over set Jell-O.
Pour remaining Jell-O mixture on top of sour cream. Return to refrigerator and allow to gel.
Serve when completely congealed.

title: coconut cake supreme
directions: Cook cake as directed on box using 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is in oven, mix creme of coconut and condensed milk.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, pierce full of holes with fork.
Spoon coconut creme mixture over and let sit until cooled.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.
Cover and put in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix remaining ingredients, except dressing, and pour in creamy Zesty Italian salad dressing.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pea pod casserole
directions: Layer in order of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or microwave 8 minutes.
Spread onion rings on paper towel and cover with a paper towel.
Heat until hot and put on top of casserole.

title: chinese beets
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
May be served hot or cold.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and salt; add boiling water.
Let it cool to lukewarm.
Mix yeast with 1 cup lukewarm water and add to Crisco/sugar mixture.
Add 2 cups flour and eggs.
Mix well. Add 4 more cups flour and mix well.
Put dough into greased bowl and let it rise for 1 hour.
Punch down and place in refrigerator until needed.
When ready to make rolls, roll out dough on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put a pat of butter on each roll and fold over to form Parker House Rolls.
Let rise for 1 hour and then bake at 375° until brown.

title: chewy butterscotch bars
directions: Bring oleo and sugar to boil; cool.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Add other ingredients.
Mix and spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and onion for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup and carrots together, then fold in zucchini.
In small bowl, mix stuffing and melted margarine.
In casserole, place 1/2 stuffing on bottom, then all of the zucchini; mix and place remaining stuffing on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed eggs
directions: Boil eggs and set aside. Melt butter in large saucepan; add flour, stirring constantly until a roux consistency. Add salt. Add canned milk, stirring constantly. Slowly add regular milk until you have a thick cream sauce.
Peel and slice hard-boiled eggs. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve over toast or biscuits. Serves 5 to 6.

title: peanut buttercream frosting
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water, peanut butter morsels; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine melted morsels, cream cheese, vanilla extract and salt; beat well.
Beat in confectioners sugar alternately with milk until mixture is spreading consistency.
Fill and frost Peanut Butter Cake.

title: charlott knox tuttle's beef and kale soup
directions: Simmer beef soup bones, meat and onions to make a broth. Strain.
Remove and discard bones and spent meat.
Add barley to the beef stock and cook for 1 hour.
Add kale to stock and barley and cook 1 more hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Coat 4 (8-ounce) ramekins with butter. In large bowl, beat together egg and half and half. Add pasta and toss to coat well. Divide pasta mixture among ramekins. Bake until firm, about 15 minutes. Invert ramekins onto baking sheet and top each with a tablespoon of sauce and a slice of cheese. Bake until the cheese melts, about 3 minutes.

title: lazy steak and potatoes
directions: Dip both sides of round steak in flour.
In a large skillet, melt butter, then add round steak.
When both sides of round steak have browned, add 3 cups of water and onion soup mix.
Bring to a boil, then turn down and let simmer.
Add sliced potatoes and let simmer until potatoes are cooked.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute onions and celery until soft.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix with deboned chicken and soups.
Top with cheese and bake in casserole dish.

title: chocolate chip crumb bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
(Mixture will be very dry and crumbly.) Press firmly into greased 7 x 11inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread evenly with caramel topping.
Bake in oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Boil chicken,
bone and cut into small pieces.
Chop eggs, celery, and onions.
Mix together chicken, eggs, celery, onions, lemon juice, cream of chicken soup and water chestnuts.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Place cheese cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and sugar in mixing bowl. Mix until smooth. Mix in vanilla. Spoon into serving bowl.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Rub lamb shanks with garlic.
Place in roasting pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix together the herbs, curry powder and bay leaf; sprinkle over shanks.
Place onion slices on top and pour soy sauce over meat.
Roast, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 300°.
Cover and roast for 2 hours.
Pour off fat, then add wine and water. Roast 1 hour more.
If you need more liquid, add wine and water. Delicious!

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Melt margarine in pan.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Coat chicken.
Place chicken skin side down in pan.
Bake in covered overproof 13x9x2 pan for 35 minutes.
Turn chicken and continue baking until done.
(Approximately 25 minutes longer.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cream cheese and milk. Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly. Serve hot with chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cherry-pineapple cobbler
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, pineapple tidbits, allspice and 1 tablespoon honey. Put into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Blend egg, sour cream and remaining 2 tablespoons honey. Stir in croutons. Spoon over cherry-pineapple mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes. If desired, top with ice cream.

title: potato ragout(serves 6)
directions: Put the bacon in a saucepan.
Cover it with cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Drain bacon and dry on paper towels.
Saute bacon in a heavy skillet for 3 to 5 minutes. Remove all but 2 tablespoons of the fat and add the onions and garlic.
Cook until the onions are transparent.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together cheeses at room temperature.
Add 1/2 cup nuts, peppers and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Coat with chili powder and nuts.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and place in large pot.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover with hot water.
Place over medium heat.
Add seasoning mix, red pepper, garlic, hot sauce, onion and oil.
Cover and boil slowly 1 hour or longer if needed.

title: no-cook banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions. Add Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk. Layer with bananas and wafers. Top with some of the Cool Whip.

title: zesty steak sauce
directions: Mix together and marinate on steak 2 to 3 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in casserole dish. Bake for 35 minutes at 350° or until top is a little puffed and browned.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place chicken in a shallow baking pan. Brush with the barbecue mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 1 hour, or until tender.
Keep basting with sauce.

title: ice tea
directions: Bring a saucepan of water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add tea bags.
Let set for 30 minutes to 1 hour, covered.
Squeeze tea bags and remove.
Add remaining ingredients to make 1 gallon of ice tea; chill.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: shells stuffed with spinach and mozzarella
directions: Prepare pasta according to package.
Cool completely. Preheat oven at 350°.
In large bowl, stir together spinach, Mozzarella, Ricotta, carrots, egg whites and pepper.
Spread bottom of pan with tomato sauce.
Stuff shells with mixture, filling each shell.
Place over tomato sauce.
Coat shells with remaining tomato sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake until center of shell is heated through about 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted margarine.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to syrup mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rainbow punch
directions: Mix 3 juices.
Chill 2 hours.
Add ginger ale at serving time, then put sherbet on top of bowl.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over beans. Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours, mixing now and again.

title: creamy orange fluff
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in oranges, pineapple and orange juice concentrate.
Coat a 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish with nonstick cooking spray; add gelatin mixture. Refrigerate until firm.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light.
Gradually add milk and pudding mix;
beat until smooth. Spread over orange layer.
Chill until firm.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. In a small bowl, mix brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Stir in melted butter until well combined.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs.
Pat remaining crumbs gently into pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix together crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix together butter and garlic.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in crumb mixture.
Roll up and place in lightly greased pan.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop squash and onion; cook until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
In a saucepan over low heat, mix well the sour cream, butter and soup.
In a casserole, layer the herb and spice mix, drained squash and onion and the sauce mix.
Continue to layer in order until all of the ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and slightly brown.
Serves 6.

title: four layer delight
directions: Make a crust with the margarine, flour and nuts; spread into a 9 x 12 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and allow to cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 1 c. Cool Whip and spread over crust. Next, spread the blueberries over the filling and top with the remaining 1 c. Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon top pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Beat in sour cream.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add to butter mixture and beat well.
Beat in vanilla.
Mix pecans, cinnamon and sugar.
Put half of pecan mixture in bottom of a tube pan.
Pour in batter; top with remaining pecan mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pompons
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt in large bowl until foamy; add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition until meringue stands in stiff peaks.
Beat in vanilla. Drop in tiny mounds, 1-inch apart, from tip of teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheets (about 1 teaspoonful is enough for each mound).
Bake in a very slow oven (250°) for about 30 minutes or until meringues are crisp and delicately golden.
Remove at once from cookie sheets; lightly press in bottom of each meringue. Cool on wire cake racks.
Cream margarine until soft; gradually beat in confectioners sugar and strawberries until thick and fluffy-smooth.
Fill meringues with strawberry mixture; press 2 together, making a pink layer between.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: old days appetizers
directions: Using toothpicks -- spear one of each & serve YUM!

title: italian cauliflower pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti and cauliflower together until spaghetti is tender.
Melt butter in frypan.
Add bread crumbs; lightly brown. Put
oil
and garlic into frypan.
Drain spaghetti and cauliflower,
reserving
1	cup of liquid.	Pour spaghetti and cauliflower
into hot oil and garlic.
Lightly fry for about 1 minute, constantly stirring "gently".

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except almonds.
Roll into a ball.
Roll in almonds.
Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter, sugar and cream cheese together. Beat in eggs (one at a time) alternating with flour.
Blend in vanilla.
Spoon batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: angel food cake delight
directions: Heat orange juice to hot and steaming (do not boil).
Dissolve sugar in hot juice.
Pour over jello and mix well.
Refrigerate to congeal.
When jello mixture begins to congeal, fold in cream or Cool Whip.
Cut frozen cake into 3 layers.
Pour Jell-O mixture over each layer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve with dollop of Cool Whip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased 13 x 9-inch or larger baking pan at 350°.
Bake until golden brown.

title: cereal sen bei
directions: Boil butter, syrup, sugar and soy sauce until sugar dissolves. Pour over mixture of Crispix, peanuts and sesame seed.
Turn into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, mixing every 15 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the water with 2 sticks margarine and 4 tablespoons of cocoa.
Sift into mixture the flour, sugar, salt and baking soda; beat until smooth.
Add sour cream, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tasty spaghetti
directions: In 3-quart pan, brown meat very well.
Drain fat.
Add olive oil to pan and brown garlic and onion.
Let cool.
Add puree and ground tomatoes.
Let cook for 1 hour.
Add tomato paste.
If sauce gets too thick, add water.
Simmer 2 hours, uncovered.
Add seasonings to mixture.
Cover and cook while cooking spaghetti. Drain spaghetti and put on a plate.
Add cheese and sauce.

title: fast chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain well.
Spray 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Cook chicken and cut into pieces.
Grate cheeses.
Place broccoli in casserole.
Cover with chicken pieces.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and grated cheeses.
Pour over top.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: lemonade or limeade
directions: Combine sugar, lemon or lime juice and 5 cups water; stir to dissolve sugar.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with lemon or lime slices, if desired.
Makes 6 (8-ounce) servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and milk in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping.
Hold cupcakes, top side down, in palm of hand. Spread whipped topping mixture on bottom and sides. Press coconut onto frosting.
Place cupcakes, top side down, on serving platter.
Drizzle with melted chocolate. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.
Makes 24 snowballs.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together confectioners sugar and flour.
Cut in butter until mix clings together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Stir well into egg mixture.
Pour over cooled crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or frost with a glaze made with lemon juice and powdered sugar. Makes 30 bars.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Add shredded cheese to mix and stir.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board and roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a biscuit cutter or use a knife to cut in squares.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 425° about 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 6 biscuits.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thick.
Stir in mayonnaise, celery seed and salt and pepper.
Pour over remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill and serve.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Separate
eggs
(yolks
from
whites).
Beat egg yolks. Mix cocoa
in
small
amount
of
hot water, then add flour to mixture and
mix
well.
Add milk and margarine to mixture and cook in iron skillet over medium heat until thick.
Let cool. Beat whites well.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Beat again.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Pour meringue and brown.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Mix the white sauce and cabbage in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with the grated cheese and fine bread crumbs. Season as desired.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until tender.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Spread this over rye slices to completely cover edges.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is slightly melted.

title: italian hors d'oeuvres pie
directions: Mix all together; pour in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Combine rhubarb and pineapple.
Turn into 8-inch square pan.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and pecans.
Mix gently and chill.

title: best cream pie
directions: Melt shortening.
Add flour, sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks. Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue made by beating the sugar into the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a moderate oven at 375° for 15 minutes or until a delicate brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
except
bread
crumbs. Place in
a well-greased casserole dish and top with buttered crumbs. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce biscuit
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening; combine egg, applesauce and sour cream. Add to dry ingredients. Mix quickly. Turn out onto floured board and knead lightly for a few seconds.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick; cut 2-inch biscuit. Place on baking sheet. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.

title: st. patrick's punch
directions: You will need a punch bowl, wooden spoon, measuring cups, ladle and plastic cups.

title: herb marinade
directions: This marinade is wonderful for chicken or fish.
Marinate for 1 to 8 hours. Serves 3 pounds.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1-1/2 quart casserole dish, stir sugar and syrup. Microwave on high 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts; microwave on high 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup; microwave on high 1 to 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be light brown and syrup hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender.
Pour into chilled glasses. Yield:
1 serving.
Serving Size:
1 cup.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples 2 to 4 hours on high.
Run cooked apples through a colander to remove seeds and peelings.
Measure pulp (per pints) and put back into crock-pot.
Add juice, sugar, allspice, cloves and cinnamon.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours, stirring every 2 hours.
Last 2 hours, leave lid off the crock-pot while cooking. Pack in jars and seal at once.

title: meringue teasers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cover cookie sheets with foil. Beat egg whites in small bowl until foamy. Gradually beat in sugar until meringue forms stiff peaks. Add vanilla and salt. Stir in nuts and chocolate. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheets. Place cookie sheets in oven. Turn oven off. Do not open oven. Leave in for 6 hours or overnight. Remove cookies from oven, foil will peel off the cookies. Store in closed container.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese; add rest of ingredients.
Use as soon as possible.
Tends to separate over time.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Combine the margarine, flour and pecans.
Press evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat in a little oil. Add onion. Combine dry ingredients. Mix Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and vinegar. Add to dry ingredients. Blend with meat and onion. Add 1 cup of water. Stir. Cover and cook on low heat for 2 hours or until meat is tender. Blend flour with other cup of water and add to meat mixture. Stir until thickened. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: peanut or pecan brittle
directions: Combine all ingredients except baking soda in large saucepan. Cook over medium-high heat to 310°, stirring constantly. When temperature reaches 310°, remove from heat; add baking soda and stir vigorously until dissolved. Pour mixture onto 2 cookie sheets sprayed with Pam cooking spray. Let cool and break into serving pieces. Use a long wooden spoon to stir because the mixture gets very
hot.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese and set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip mixture.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Freeze.
Remove 1 hour before serving. Store covered in freezer.

title: country chicken pie
directions: Prepare Dill Pastry.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place carrots, onion, celery, green pepper and water in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan; cover and cook over medium heat about 3 minutes.
Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat; blend in flour.
Gradually add broth and milk to flour mixture; cook, stirring, until thick, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add chicken, peas, salt and ground pepper.
Cook until hot, about 2 minutes.
Pour chicken mixture into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Roll pastry on a lightly floured surface into 7-inch square.
Cut pastry into 4 squares and place on top of chicken mixture.
Bake until pastry is golden, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add milk and mix. Pour into ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Cover with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until set.
Serve with whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Serves a lot.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients and layer into a buttered 9 X 13 dish.

title: yum yum fruit salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and pudding, fruit cocktail, oranges and grapes.
Mix in marshmallow.
Chill!
Add sliced banana just before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well. Chill 24 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil. Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Combine alternately with carrots and pineapple.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 3 small well-greased loaf pans or 6 medium size cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less, if smaller pans are used. Cans, 50 minutes.

title: jeri's best and easiest punch
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and pour over ice.
For extra party look, pour over ice ring.
Makes 24 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to the package directions. Rinse and drain. Mix all other ingredients together except vegetables. After well blended, mix with vegetables and then add macaroni. Refrigerate at least one hour before you serve.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add pizza sauce, garlic salt and oregano leaves.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan or large, deep dish and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and evaporated milk 9 minutes after it comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat; add Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips.
Mix well and pour into well-greased pan.
Cool.

title: ida mae's potato salad
directions: Heat mayonnaise slowly to heated stage.
When mayonnaise moves away from side of pan, it is done.
(This is the secret for mom's famous potato salad.)
Mix with ingredients, adding salt and pepper.

title: caramel bars
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Line bottom of pan with soda crackers.
Boil together for 3 minutes the brown sugar and butter or oleo.
Spread over crackers evenly.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Allow to melt completely.
Spread over top and sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Cool.
Cut or break apart.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Pour sour cream in mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.
Add additional milk or cream if a thinner dressing is desired.

title: rice amandine
directions: Cook and stir onion in hot butter until tender. Add broth, lemon juice and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil. Stir in rice. Bring to a heavy boil, then reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in green
beans, almonds and dill.
Cover. Let stand for about 5 minutes, then serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from each fruit, keeping about 2 cups.
Then mix juice and pudding mix with mixer.
Add to fruit mixture and serve cold.
Delicious!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Add oil, egg whites, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add nuts and apples.
Pour into lightly greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
Do not flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt,
cocoa,
soda
and spices.
Add applesauce and oil.
Stir until
smooth.
Pour
into a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Bake 60 minutes.
After 30 minutes of baking time elapses sprinkle chocolate chips on top and resume baking.

title: wassail bowl with baked apple punch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut apples in half crosswise and place cut side down in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes or until the apple halves are fork-tender.
Meanwhile, in covered 6-quart saucepot over low heat, simmer 2 cups apple cider, cloves, allspice and nutmeg 10 minutes.
Add remaining apple cider, undiluted lemonade and orange juice concentrates and brown sugar. Heat until hot, but not boiling, stirring occasionally.
Pour hot cider mixture from saucepot into heated large punch bowl.
Float apples, skin side up, in punch.
Sprinkle top with a little sugar.

title: sausage strata
directions: Place bread in bottom of greased 9-inch square baking dish. Place sausage over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: olive and artichoke tapanade
directions: **Toast walnuts at 350° for 5-10 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except confectioners sugar and beat well.
Pour batter into two greased bread pans. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool about 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: easy cream puffs
directions: Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together. Add pineapple and blend.
Cut cookies with a serrated knife and fill.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: praline sundae sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Stir in cream and nuts. Serve warm or cold over ice cream.

title: cheezy chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in soup for 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat.

title: swedish apple nut pie
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time. You do not need a mixer for this.
Pour into a greased pie tin. Sprinkle top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.
This freezes very well.
Cook it first and then reheat.
These are simple to make and with a stack of aluminum pie tins and a bushel of apples, you can have your freezer filled in no time.

title: fruit dip (ii)
directions: Mix together and serve with cut up fruit.

title: easy cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar, add egg and mix well.
Add soda and vanilla, mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts and coconut, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients; stir and refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Pour all ingredients over chops.
Bake 2 hours in 375° oven or until well done.

title: volcano potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with cooking oil; bake in a 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.
Cut the top off each potato and scoop out the contents into a mixing bowl, saving the skins.
Add cheese, butter, milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Pile potato mixture back into the skins and sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven until browned.
Serves 4.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Cook meat, seasoned salt, taco seasoning, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chilies.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Mix Ricotta cheese, Monterey jack cheese and eggs; set aside.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows: 1/3 meat, tortillas (one layer, cut to fit) and 1/3 Ricotta mixture.
Repeat 2 more times.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: orange slice cake
directions: *Reserve 1/2 cup flour for sliced candy.

title: white beans, creole style
directions: Soak beans about 4 hours or overnight.
Drain and cover with water; bring to a boil, then simmer about 30 minutes.
While beans are simmering, cut ham from bone, chop onion and brown together in oil (slowly).
When brown, add 2 cups water and cut green onions. Simmer.
After beans have simmered for 30 minutes, drain; then add the onion and ham mixture.
Add enough water to cover; salt and add peppers and Tabasco sauce.
Cook slowly until done, about 1 hour.
The ham bone may be added with the beans when the seasoning is added.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix all ingredients in large kettle.
Cook until hot.
Fill jars and process about
15 minutes.
It can also be frozen.
You may want to cut back on the sugar.
The full amount makes it very sweet.

title: barbecue roast
directions: Mix all ingredients except roast to make barbecue sauce.
Add roast.
Simmer until done, turning occasionally.
Cook until tender.

title: cucumber cups filled with herbed yogurt and smoked salmon
directions: Drain yogurt in a fine sieve set over a bowl with its surface covered with plastic wrap and chilled overnight.

Cut the cucumber crosswise into sixteen 3/4-inch pieces and, with a melon ball cutter, scoop out the centers, forming 1/4-inch thick cups. Sprinkle the cucumber cups with salt and let them drain, inverted, on paper towels for 10 minutes.

title: ba's sloppy joes
directions: Brown all the meat together with onion and celery.
Drain off excess fat.
Add seasoning packet and mushrooms; mix well with meat.
Add ketchup and barbecue sauce and mix well.
Simmer over low heat for approximately 10 minutes.
Serve on your choice of roll.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover.
When tender, remove from water and remove bones when cool enough.
While chicken is cooking, make dumplings.
Put flour in a bread tray or large bowl. Make a hole in the center and break egg into it.
Add warm water. Mix together with the flour to form a pliable ball.
Separate into 3 balls.
Roll out to desired thickness on a floured surface. Cut into squares or strips.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add dumplings slowly and stir.
Add extra hot water if needed and stir.
Add chicken and boiled eggs.
Cook for 10 or 15 minutes. Stir.
Turn heat off.
Ready to serve.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak beans in the water overnight in the slow cooker.
Do not drain.
Cover and cook on high about 3 hours, until very tender. Add remaining ingredients except salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Remove ham, cut up meat and return to soup.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
More water may be added if soup seems too thick.
Serve piping hot in large soup bowls.
A meal in itself.
Served in the US Senate Cafe.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat eggs very well.
Add corn, sugar, salt and milk.
Cut oleo in pieces and mix with other ingredients, leaving a few pieces for the top.
Pour in baking dish and cook in oven at 450° about 50 minutes or until firm.

title: sally's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole. Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is easy to double or triple.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; place in a shallow container or a heavy-duty zip top plastic bag.
Add chicken; cover or seal and chill 1 to 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Grill, covered over medium coals (300° to 400°) for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a 9-inch clay or plastic pot and a small dirt shovel.

title: chicken breasts parmesan
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy skillet. Dredge chicken breasts in a mixture of bread crumbs, all but 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and parsley. Coat with beaten egg and redredge in crumbs. Cook over medium heat until golden brown on both sides. Cover with tight-fitting lid and simmer on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Drain on paper toweling.

title: frogmore stew
directions: NOTE: Use 1 potato, 1/2 lb. shrimp and 1 corn on the cob per person. Corn can be fresh or frozen, cut in half.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts, then dice.
In a saucepan, mix Ro-Tel, soup and the Velveeta until cheese is melted.
Then add beans, chili powder and chicken.
In a casserole dish, cover the bottom with a layer of the sauce, then a layer of chips (or shells). Continue and end with sauce.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cold german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until just done.
Drain water.
Slice potatoes while warm, handling carefully.
Mix all other ingredients well (until sugar is dissolved); pour over warm potatoes.
Stir carefully.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: roasted red pepper dip
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise into quarters, discarding cores, seeds and ribs.
Bring skin side up about 6-inches from heat until skin is blackened, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and wrap in aluminum foil.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove skin.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: incredible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix until crumbly the cake mix, butter and egg; reserve 1 cup. Press rest into a 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.

title: sausage strata
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread bread with butter or margarine.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Brown sausage; drain well.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Set out 15 minutes before baking at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 8.

title: turkey chili
directions: Cook turkey, onions and garlic in Dutch oven over medium flame; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except kidney beans, almonds and cheese.
Bring to a boil over high flame.
Reduce flame to simmer, cover and cook 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and almonds.
Simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Garnish with shredded cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand at room temperature for 8 hours.
Stir now and then to dissolve sugar, then refrigerate. These keep well up to 6 months.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper in a large pot.
Cut up tomatoes; add to the pot with their juice.
Add taco seasoning, dressing mix, picante sauce, tomato paste, corn, beans, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve in bowls; sprinkle each serving with tortilla chips.
Cover with cheese.
Makes a large pot, about 12 servings.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and mix until creamy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt called for.
Drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in baking dish. Stir together soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg, stirring to blend.
Pour over broccoli.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until heated and bread crumbs brown, about 35 minutes.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Bake roast in oven at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Boil noodles in measured water with the bouillon cubes.
Cook until noodles are tender.
Cut roast into noodles.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Depending on size to feed.
Broil chicken until done.
Cook rice until done.
Simmer soup until heated through.
Cut up chicken in pieces.
You pick size.
Put rice in casserole dish and spread on bottom.
Cover rice with soup, leaving little to spread over top.
Put chicken on top of rice and soup.
Spread soup over top.
Sprinkle poultry seasoning over top and serve hot.

title: salmon patties
directions: Break up salmon into small pieces with a fork.
Add egg, milk, crumbs and onion.
Form into patties.
Roll in flour and fry in oil or butter.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Make a dressing of the eggs, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thickened; add an 8 ounce package of tiny marshmallows to the hot dressing.
Stir until melted.
Let cool.
Add the Cool Whip; mix well and then add fruit cocktail and bananas.
Then put in freezer.

title: saucy zucchini bake
directions: Cut zucchini into medium thin wheels; slice mushrooms. Lightly saute together in oil with garlic and spices until tender. In a casserole, grease with olive oil.
Pour mix into casserole; stir in grated cheese and tomato paste.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Cover and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Take foil off and return to oven for about 5 more minutes.

title: cheese and sausage dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler or crock-pot.
Do not boil. Brown sausage in skillet with water.
Drain water off after browned.
Blend tomatoes until fine.
Mix all ingredients and serve hot.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown over medium heat.

title: fiesta squash
directions: Melt the margarine in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients until tender, stirring occasionally.
Cook, covered, over low heat.

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and vanilla and beat.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add to egg mixture along with dates and nuts.
Use small amount of buttermilk if more moisture needed.
Drop onto cookie sheet sprayed with cooking spray and bake at 325° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot juice
directions: Use electric juicer to run all vegetables through.
Juice should be taken as soon as it is juiced, so all vitamins will not be lost.
If not drunk at time of juicing, cap tight and store in refrigerator not over 1 day.
Should make 8 or 10 ounces.

title: pickled beets(canning recipe)
directions: After beets are cooked, cool enough to handle.
Remove skins. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Pack into sterilized jars.
Cover with vinegar and sugar syrup.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water (to jar neck).
Seal.

title: vegetarian pate
directions: Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and thyme at medium heat in saucepan sprayed with vegetable oil; cook until all appearance of liquid is gone.
While this is cooking, combine almonds, olive oil and extract in food processor.
Add mushroom mixture and continue to process until smooth.
Slowly add balsamic vinegar while processing.
Chill in fridge.
Use it as a traditional pate, stuff mushrooms, crusty bread or crackers.

title: mrs. lillian redmond's ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain and add flour, soup mix, water and tomato sauce.
Mix well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add drained macaroni and pour into Pyrex dish. Top with grated cheese and heat in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: mound candy
directions: Mix milk, coconut, sugar and margarine.
Chill 2 hours.
Form balls and chill 2 hours.

title: south of the border enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain well.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato paste, water, onion and salt.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced. Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons meat mixture on each tortilla.
Roll tightly and place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread cheese over top on enchiladas.
Sprinkle with green chilies.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak bread in milk for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, butter and salt.
Pour mixture slowly over eggs.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup raisins, if desired.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water for about 1 hour, or until firm.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil 8 minutes each side.
Remove from heat. Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute.
Add garlic, wine and vinegar. Cook on medium heat.
Almost all evaporated 5 minutes.
Stir in broth, basil, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes into onion mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Cook on low 25 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Heat liquid to a boil for 5 minutes. Add olives and parsley to sauce.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: ham stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti.
Set aside.
In a large skillet saute onion in oil.
Remove from heat.
Add ham, drained mushrooms, half of Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.
In a saucepan saute green peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until thoroughly combined.
Add milk.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Mix a quarter of sauce into ham mixture.
Stuff shells with about 1/3 cup of filling.
Place in a greased baking dish. Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: handy dough
directions: Combine ingredients and blend thoroughly with hands.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Let rise in pans 2 hours before baking. Roll out and make nut rolls or any other filling will work.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and chilies.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Cut into small blocks and put in bowl.
After melting, put cheese in crock-pot. Stir in sausage and green chilies.
Simmer on low.
Serve on top of tortilla chips.

title: red velvet coconut cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to directions on box.
Add the food coloring, vanilla and salt, blending well.
Bake as directed; cool and frost.

title: deep dish chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour, bouillon and pepper.
Over medium heat, gradually add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuit mix.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions for rolled biscuits. Roll out to cover top of dish; cut slits near center.
Place dough over filling; turn under edge, seal and flute.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack before slicing.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together; set aside.
Cream shortening.
Stir sugar and molasses into shortening.
Add egg yolk; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Chill dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Cut cookies.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and decorate.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Into a 1-quart casserole dish, place a layer of cracker crumbs.
Next a layer of asparagus.
Mix the soup with the evaporated milk and put on top of the asparagus.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. The cracker crumbs absorb the moisture and give a cheesy base.

title: amish brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles and drain well.
In oval baking dish, combine soup, evaporated milk and tuna.
Add noodles and stir until coated.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned on top and set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
May be frozen.
Makes 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: curry rice salad
directions: Drain artichokes and save juices.
Cut artichokes in half; combine with mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Fix Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
Cool rice.
Mix rice and artichoke liquid, then add remaining ingredients.
Toss; chill and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: pasta delight
directions: Boil noodles in water until tender.
Mix tuna, chopped vegetables and garlic.
Add to noodles.
Pour dressing over mixture and toss lightly.
Add garlic toast and you have a great summer meal.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving pieces.
Brown in a baking pan over surface heat.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the ribs; cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 3/4 hours or until done. Baste the ribs 2 or 3 times during baking.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Smaller amounts may be used.

title: chocolate surprise salad
directions: Put pineapple in bowl first. Add cherries, marshmallows, nuts and chocolate chips; mix lightly. Sprinkle pudding over and mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill and serve.
Serves 10 or more.

title: torpedos
directions: Grind onions, pepperoni and green pepper in meat grinder.
Put all other ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat on stove for 3 hours.
Serve in hot dog rolls.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat 10 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan 1 hours at 350°.

title: ranch snack mix
directions: In large bowl, add all snacks.
Sprinkle with dressing mix; toss gently.
Drizzle with oil; toss until coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into a buttered dish.

title: apple tapioca
directions: Arrange apples in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook mixture until it comes to a boil.
Pour over apples.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Cook pudding and milk; cool.
Must be real cool.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove shells and cut eggs in half. Remove yolk and add all other ingredients, except paprika.
The mixture will be pasty. Spoon into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika, decorate with parsley.

title: eston's meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, bread and eggs. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Mix.
Spread ketchup over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's angel roll
directions: Grease bottom of a jelly roll pan.
Line pan with waxed paper and grease again.
Prepare angel food batter and turn half of batter into pan and spread into corners.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Use rest of batter for cupcakes.
Cool and invert cake on towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Remove waxed paper and roll in towel. Beat remaining ingredients until thick.
Unroll cake; fill with whipped cream and roll again.
Frost with additional whipped cream and chill.

title: grape nuts custard
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl to mushy stage.
Pour into casserole pan or dish.
Place custard dish in large pan which has water on the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
When done, you should be able to take fork and pull firm custard from edge of pan.

title: peanut no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to mix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool until set.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine peanut butter and butter in a large mixing bowl, blending well. Gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beating well. Stir in almond extract.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and add sugar.
Cool.
Add lemon and pineapple juices.
Freeze in milk cartons.
Thaw to a slush and add 2-quarts 7-Up or Mountain Dew.
Scoops of sherbet on top add a nice touch.

title: cheesy stuffed peppers
directions: Core peppers and steam in microwave; saute onions.
Add sausage and brown, then drain.
Add 1 small jar Cheez Whiz, tomatoes and cooked rice to this mixture.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Arrange in a Pyrex container and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: cheryl's sweet steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Flour and fry in skillet with oil until brown. Salt and pepper to taste.
Line bottom of nonstick baking pan with a layer of Prego sauce.
Sprinkle layer with the 2 tablespoons of onions. Add layer of steak. Cover steak with layer of brown sugar. Continue (in same order), layering ingredients.
Cover top with brown sugar.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
May be prepared and slow cooked in crock-pot. Cook until meat is tender.

title: crunchy asparagus with onions
directions: Slice asparagus diagonally.
Place oil in wok and heat.
Add asparagus, onions and other seasonings.
Cover and shake until crispy, about 6 or 8 minutes.

title: easy broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
In 10 x 6-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of the broccoli, 1/2 of the soup mixture and 1/2 can of the onions.
Top with remaining broccoli and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes.

title: hot beef cheese roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Brush each with melted butter.
Mix chipped beef, cheese, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce together, then divide evenly and spread on the 4 rectangles. Roll up each rectangle and cut into 4 slices.
Place seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes. Serve hot.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: ham and cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cheesecake (baked)
directions: Grease 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan; dust with graham cracker crumbs.
With mixer on high speed, mix cottage cheese and cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Beat in sugar, then eggs; with mixer on low speed beat in next 3 ingredients.
Then beat in margarine and sour cream until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake in 325° oven for about 70 minutes or until firm around edge.
Turn off oven.
Let cake stand in oven 2 hours.
Remove and chill.
Remove side of pan.
If desired, cover with strawberries and glaze or blueberries and glaze.

title: turkey chip bake
directions: Arrange the first 8 ingredients lightly in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese and potato sticks.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: 15 minute chicken and rice dinner
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Remove chicken.

title: polenta dolce
directions: Combine milk, sugar and lemon rind in saucepan.
Heat until warm.
Slowly add Cream of Wheat and cook for 8 to 10 minutes. Slowly stir in lemon juice, egg yolks and lemon extract.
Cook for 1 more minute.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight or at least until very firm.
Cut into 2-inch diamonds or squares.
Blend in eggs and cracker meal.
Use egg whites left and 2 whole eggs, beat well.
Fry in oil until golden brown. Drain on brown paper.
You can sprinkle sugar on top.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
At low speed, gradually add flour, then sugar, mixing until well blended.
By hand, stir in frosting mix and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour batter into greased pan, tube or Bundt.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before serving.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Clean and wash chicken. Take off skin and fat. Put in pot with no oil. Add salt, pepper and bouillon cubes. Start on low heat (chicken will make water). Stir well and cook until tender. You may need to add a little water. Fry down to brown. Add leftover cooked rice to pot after you take out chicken and mix together to make sticky rice.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs; stir in the bananas.
Mix flour and soda; add buttermilk, vanilla and nuts. Pour in greased pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Mix together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, brown sugar, nuts and diced rhubarb.
Beat egg; add buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Pour over flour mixture; mix well.
Grease muffin tins. Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: hot dog appetizers
directions: Melt jelly.
Add mustard and hot dogs. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Keep heated.
Serve warm.

title: dad's homemade pizza
directions: Mix pizza dough and let rise in warm oven.
Brown hamburger and sausage in skillet separately.
Follow directions on pizza mix.
Top pizza with hamburger, sausage and grated cheese.
Cook pizza and enjoy.

title: vegetable clam chowder
directions: Scrape carrots; set aside.
Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces; set aside.
Peel onion and cut into thin slices; set aside.
Chop parsley.
Drain clams and reserve juice; set aside. Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add carrots, potatoes, onions, tomatoes, lima beans, salt, pepper and thyme.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Heat oil in skillet; stir in flour.
Add clam juice, mixing until thick.
Stir clam juice and oil into vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add clams and parsley.
Taste to correct seasonings.

title: lo-cal broccoli-ham soup
directions: In
a
quart
pan,
cook the chopped onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, chicken bouillon, mustard, thyme
and	pepper.
Add milk and water all at once. Cook
and stir
over	medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Stir
broccoli and
ham
into
saucepan.	Return	to boiling. Reduce
heat; simmer
for
to 6 minutes, until broccoli is tender
and
soup is	heated	through, stirring occasionally. Makes 4 servings. Each serving is 299 calories.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Slice angel food cake into thin layers.
Place a layer of cake, then add enough pineapple to cover cake.
Then pour vanilla pudding over the pineapple.
Repeat as many times as desired and finally cover with Cool Whip.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture boils. Cook for 1 minute; remove from heat and set aside.
In a skillet, brown pork chops in oil.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, brown sugar and peanut butter together in large mixer bowl on low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup of mixture and set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, carrots and water; cook until tender.
Melt margarine in large saucepan; add onions.
Saute until translucent.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Pour in milk and stir until thickened.
When potatoes are tender, dip out some of the water; pour flour mixture into potatoes and stir until mixed well.
If too thick, add some of the water back until of desired consistency.
Reheat until hot.

title: mocha drop cookies
directions: Blend until light.
Mix all together.
Drop on cookie sheets. Bake at 375°.

title: rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water together and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine first three ingredients, then add yeast mixture and egg.
Place a lid on your bowl and refrigerate about 15 minutes.
Fill muffin pan half full and bake at 350° until done.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture and beat well. Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Add nuts. Put dough in waxed paper lined loaf pans and place in refrigerator overnight. Slice and bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs and mix with sugar.
Add to melted margarine.
Mix well.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Mix with nuts and dates.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread in greased pan (8 x 12 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, depending on oven. Mixture will be thick.
When done, cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar if desired.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix well with 1 package of cooked noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, blend sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, margarine and peanut butter.
Bring to a boil and cook for 6 minutes or 230° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from fire, add vanilla and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until very thick.
Pour into well-greased glass dish (Pam works well).
Let cool and cut into squares.
This fudge freezes very well in a tightly closed plastic container.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, mix the cocoa, sugar, corn syrup, cream or milk, salt and butter.
Stir over low heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Sauce may be refrigerated in a covered container.
Reheat in microwave or hot water before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: The day before:
Fry in oil and drain separately, almonds, sesame seed and saifon.
Mix together salad dressing, made up of oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Stew 1 chicken.
Cool, bone and refrigerate.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Stir together flour, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine. Remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Stir dry ingredients and walnuts into brown sugar mixture. Spread batter in prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cut into bars while warm. Makes 48.

title: pizza pockets
directions: Middle:
In a small saucepan, heat vegetable oil on high for 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Add cheese and tomato sauce.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: lamb layer casserole pie
directions: Combine lamb, onion, soup and peas in 2-quart buttered casserole.
Season.
Sprinkle herbs and rind.
Top with layer of potatoes and tomatoes.
Roll out pie crust (according to package directions).
Cut into 3/4-inch strips.
Crisscross strips over tomatoes.
Pinch edges.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Place all ingredients into bowl except apples.
Beat until smooth.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured tube pan. Cover with a layer of sliced apples.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon and sugar.
Repeat a layer of batter then another layer of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top layer of apples. Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: old fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Boil together molasses and butter. Cool. Add ginger, baking soda and flour. Roll dough thin on floured board and cut with cookie cutters. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: *Measure oatmeal and blend in a blender to a fine powder.

title: sweet potatoes supreme
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in skins 20 minutes and then peel.
Peel and slice the apples.
Boil orange juice, salt, sugar, butter and cornstarch until clear.
Put layer of potatoes in bottom of large casserole.
Add a layer of apples.
Pour half of sauce over apples. Repeat, having apples on top.
Pour balance of sauce over and bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes or until apples are done.

title: pie crust
directions: Place flour and salt in bowl.
With fork, cut in shortening, until the size of small peas.
Sprinkle water in until moist firm ball.
Flatten and roll from center to edge.
Place in pan, cut edges with knife. Pinch edge.
Fill.

title: hopscotch crunchie
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter on low heat. Remove from heat and stir. Add chow mein noodles and marshmallows. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper lined cookie sheet. Chill until set.
Yields about 30 crunchies.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring undiluted soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese; heat until melted.
Dissolve gelatin in water; add to mixture.
Cool.
Add the mayonnaise, onion, celery and shrimp to the first mixture. Spray mold with Pam.
Put mixture in mold; refrigerate overnight.

title: tomato salad topping
directions: Simply mix everything together and put over chicken cutlets, veal cutlets or your favorite fish.
Tomato Salad Topping is best on Italian bread toasted (small squares).

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease pan with butter or oil.
In a large bowl, mix 2 cups of flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and butter in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquid is very warm (120° to 130°).
Butter doesn't need to melt.
Gradually add dry ingredients and beat two minutes at medium speed of electric mixer or use hands.
Add eggs and 3/4 cup of flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto table and cover the dough with butter.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Roll the dough up and cut into slices.
Put into greased pan.
Cover with hot towel and let rise.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve hot or warm.
Good.

title: blintz souffle(from russia)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole dish or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place blintzes over butter in one layer, seam side down.
Blend other ingredients with well beaten eggs and pour over blintzes.
Bake for 45 minutes or until tops start to brown.

title: chrissy's crunchy bagel delight
directions: Place heaping tablespoon of tunafish on slightly toasted bagel. Put tomato slice on top of tuna. Place cheese slice on top of tomato. Place in toaster oven, until cheese is melted.
Enjoy this refreshing bagel for lunch or even a snack.

title: summertime salad
directions: In a large bowl, break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Add drained vegetables, then cheese or ham or both, if you wish.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and sugar.
Pour over salad.
Toss lightly, coating all.
Serve with a roll and beverage for a nice lunch. Makes enough for a picnic.
Store leftover in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Over very low heat, melt chocolate.
Cool slightly.
In food processor puree all ingredients except chocolate until smooth.
Add melted chocolate.
Blend well. Pour into lightly buttered 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until just set.
Makes 16 squares.
May be sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: chicken in lemon sauce
directions: Add oil to flat roasting pan, enough to cover bottom of pan. Rolling chicken pieces in oil, arrange evenly in pan.
Sprinkle first garlic powder lightly over chicken, lightly salt then sprinkle dried chopped oregano (enough so that each piece has several chopped pieces).
If dried oregano is used sprinkle lightly over each piece of chicken.
Oven fry at 350° for 40 minutes.
