While chicken is cooking, squeeze 2 to 3 lemons, strain after 40 minutes of chicken being cooked, spoon lemon juice over each piece of chicken.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange bread slices into two layers.

title: rice-a-la-bella
directions: Saute onion and carrots.
Cook rice per directions on box.
Add sugar; saute fruit and nuts and put sauteed items on top of the rice.

title: jumbo raisin cookie
directions: Boil raisins and water on stove.
Cream together oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Cut up bacon into thirds.
Place 1 or 2 (depending on size) water chestnuts in a piece of bacon and roll-up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place on broiling pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Remove and put in casserole dish.
Mix ketchup and sugar.
Pour mixture over bacon wraps.
Heat in oven to warm.
Remove.
Can leave in casserole dish or remove pieces to other dish for serving.

title: speedy chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken in oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until no longer pink, 5 minutes.
Add red pepper. Cook until chicken is cooked through and pepper is tender-crisp, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and milk; cook, stirring, until heated through.
Serve over toast.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and crackers.
Place in baking dish.
Crumble crackers and place on top of casserole. Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dessert grillers
directions: Arrange fruit on 12 wooden skewers. Spread margarine evenly on both sides of pound cake. Mix sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle over cake. Place cake on grill over hot coals or on rack of broiler pan. Heat on both sides until lightly toasted. Cool. Serve with cool whip and fruit kabobs.

title: pickled pasta
directions: Blend all in blender (except noodles) until liquid.
Cook trio noodles in salt water.
Rinse with cold water.
Pour liquid over noodles and refrigerate.
Let salad marinate for 1 hour or more.

title: low calorie whipped topping
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Stir nonfat dry milk into skim milk in saucepan.
Heat to simmering.
Add softened gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add vanilla and sugar. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat with electric mixer until very thick and light.
Serve on fresh fruit.
Topping can be stored in refrigerator or can be frozen.
Makes 2 cups topping. Contains 5 calories per tablespoon.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350°.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Mix powdered sugar with mashed potatoes. Add vanilla and mix until it is like pie dough. Roll out in shape of pie crust with a rolling pin. Spread with peanut butter. Roll up small and cut in slices, about 1/2-inch thick. Place on large platter and put in refrigerator until chilled.

title: barbecue sauce italiano
directions: In medium saucepan combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken on grill fat side down.
Sprinkle with garlic salt or powder.
Grill 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn and sprinkle with garlic salt or powder.
Grill 15 minutes longer.

title: french hot chocolate
directions: Combine the chocolates, sugar, milk and cream in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir frequently with a wire whisk or wooden spoon until the chocolate melts and the sugar dissolves.
Heat until just under the boiling point.
Remove from the heat and beat in a blender or with a rotary beater until smooth and frothy.
Add the vanilla and serve hot.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms until tender. Add spinach and ham, cook until moisture is evaporated.
Cool slightly;
Beat eggs, add cheese and mix well.
Stir into spinach mixture and add salt and pepper to taste. Spread in 9 inch pie pan or Quiche dish. Bake in 350 degree oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pea soup andersen's
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients and boil hard for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes longer or until peas are tender.
Strain soup through a fine sieve and reheat.
Taste for seasoning.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
Serve hot with warm bread, if desired.

title: low-fat crunchy cinnamon chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use kitchen scissors and cut tortillas in half (2 at a time, if you prefer) and cut each half into 3 wedges.
Place wedges on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl mix together cinnamon, sugar and Molly McButter.
Generously sprinkle wedges with sugar mix.
Spray nonstick cooking spray very lightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes.
These burn easily so watch carefully.
One gram fat and 119 calories per serving.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat undiluted broccoli soup and frozen broccoli until broccoli is thawed.
In skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon oil, cook carrots and onion until vegetables are tender.
Remove to bowl.
In same skillet in 3 tablespoons oil, cook mushrooms until brown and all liquid has evaporated.
Stir in carrot mixture.
Prepare noodles as label directs; drain.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in greased casserole.
Test with knife.
When knife is clean, it's done.

title: artichoke-spinach dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Top with paprika and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in ball.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Roll in 1/2 cup pecans, chopped fine.

title: garden vegetable casserole
directions: Place all sliced vegetables in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients; toss lightly.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken fantastic
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese and crumbs.
Mix well.
Pour into baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with grated cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared the day before and refrigerated.
Save buttered crumbs to sprinkle over casserole just before it goes into oven.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: hershey almond bar pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in double boiler or in microwave oven. Put Cool Whip in bowl large enough to stir.
Add melted chocolate to Cool Whip and fold to mix well.
(Do not stir vigorously or Cool Whip will lose its volume.)
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: herb shaker #2
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in a tightly capped jar or in a salt and pepper shaker.
Use at your table instead of salt.
This is especially good on fresh pork, poultry, beef, carrots, squash, sweet potatoes, beets and corn.

title: veggie delight
directions: Prepare asparagus and mixed vegetables according to package directions.
Cook meatless patty in microwave or on stove top according to directions; crumble.
Heat rice and add sauce and stir.
Place rice in a bowl; mix in patty crumbles and all vegetables.
Add salt and pepper if desired.
Makes one serving.

title: "libby's" coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions; poke holes in top of cake.
Mix cream of coconut and milk.
Pour over top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut flakes.

title: ida maude's apple pie
directions: Mix fruits in baking dish.
Cover with dry cake mix and nuts. Melt butter and pour on top.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: three lettuce salad
directions: In a screw-top jar, combine olive oil, vinegar, garlic and salt. Cover.
Shake until well blended.
Chill until serving.

title: my golden cubed pickles
directions: Pare and
quarter
cukes.
Remove
seeds. Cut in cubes. Chop onions and red
peppers.
Put
in kettle with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour vinegar over mixture and mix well.
Mix turmeric, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and salt and add to kettle.
Mix
well	and
cook
slowly at simmering temperature until pieces are tender
and can be pierced with fork.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pizza in a bowl
directions: Brown
beef, onion, peppers and mushrooms; drain.
Then season with salt and pepper.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer. When shell
macaroni is done cooking, pour in casserole dish, then
add beef mixture.
Top with cheese and pepperoni slices. Bake in
oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges are browned.

title: fancy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk in a large bowl. Mix on low speed with mixer until thick. Add the sour cream and mix well for 2 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip until well blended. Place a layer of wafers in the bottom of a large deep bowl, then a layer of sliced bananas, a layer of pudding mixture and continue to layer in this order. Top with vanilla wafer crumbs. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture with milk,
Mix until blended well.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the middle of cake comes out clean.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix in large bowl dates, sugar, butter and water.
Stir until butter melts.
Cool.
Stir in the egg, soda, flour, nuts and rum. Put in a buttered loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean in a 350° oven.
For a sweeter bread, double nuts, rum and sugar.
Great served with cream cheese.
Slices best when allowed to sit overnight.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet cook beef and onion.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms, cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream. Serve over noodles.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Roll into balls; set until firm.
Dip into chocolate almond bark.

title: lime mold
directions: Mix the cream cheese and milk until creamy.
Add hot juice to Jell-O.
Stir in cream cheese until dissolved. Chill until it starts to thicken (about 7 minutes).
Add Cool Whip and nuts. Chill in a large mold pan until firm.

title: baked garlic chicken
directions: First squeeze the lemon over the chicken.
Put butter or margarine in a large skillet and fry the entire chicken 5 minutes on each side.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into pan lined with wax paper.
Leave in refrigerator 48 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add the next 5 ingredients. Mix and chill for easier rolling.
Roll on floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: battered peppers
directions: Cut peppers into strips.
Cut cheese into strips.
Wrap peppers around cheese and dip in batter.
Fry in deep, hot grease. May use either hot or sweet peppers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and cool.
Mix spaghetti, Italian dressing and Kroger salad seasoning.
Cut tomatoes, onions and green pepper in small pieces and add to spaghetti.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Blend cream cheese with sugar.
In another bowl, mix together pineapple, strawberries, bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Combine the two mixtures.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Cover and freeze.
Slice and serve.

title: loving yellow cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla to milk. Fold in flour alternately with milk, making about 4 additions of each.
Pour into 8-inch greased pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with joy!
Yields two 8-inch layers.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine flour and baking powder in a bowl.
Make a well in the center and add remaining ingredients.
Mix with fingers or fork until ingredients are well blended.
Roll on a floured board as thinly as possible.
Let dry for one hour.
Cut in strips the width of noodle you want.
Then stack strips and cut.
Let dry. Can be frozen.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and spices.
Add raisins and oats.
In a separate bowl, mix the applesauce, eggs, oil and sweetener.
Beat well.
Add the two mixtures together. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on desired dessert.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
The sauce is ready for the chickens.
There is enough sauce for 3 chickens.

title: baked bean trio
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon in crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple date cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and apple pie filling (chopped some).
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese delight
directions: Cube bread.
Layer bread and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and mustard and pour over the top of bread and cheese.
Let stand at least 1 hour or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: crescent cheese souffle
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press dough over bottom of pan and one inch up on sides to make crust.
Press perforations and seams well.
Combine in large bowl the eggs, milk, cheese and seasonings; mix well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice onion and potatoes in thin slices.
Place alternating in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over potatoes and onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: * supreme skillet chicken *
directions: Cut zucchini in half, lengthwise, and slice diagonally in 1/2-inch pieces.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup and seasonings.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini and tomatoes; cook 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: easy mint patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine corn syrup, softened butter or margarine and peppermint extract.
Add powdered sugar, about 1 cup at a time, stirring until well blended.

title: mystery dessert
directions: Mix the margarine, flour and 3/4 cup pecans together.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Make pudding according to package directions and let cool. Add pudding to cake mix; add 2 eggs and 3/4 cup oil.
Mix with mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top with butterscotch chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
before adding crackers.	Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Ovens vary; check temperature.

title: fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Mix well. Stir in sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in 7 1/2 x 12-inch buttered pan.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart, buttered casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
If desired, you may add onion, sausage, peppers, tomatoes, etc. (cooked).
Great for a crowd for breakfast.
Just double the recipe.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add jello; cool slightly.
Add fresh strawberries.
When mixture is cool, put in pie shell and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: wally carlson's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce. Chill until partially set.
Add celery or cauliflower and nuts or bananas.
Pour into a 4-cup mold and chill until firm.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: In a large bowl mix eggs, soup, cheese, cooked onions and shrimp.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Test for doneness, when center springs back at touch of your finger.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Stir in cooled, melted Baker's chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at high speed for 5 minutes after each addition.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours) or freeze.

title: almond-cherry circles
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and almond extract.
Turn out onto floured surface; knead gently 8 to 10 strokes.
Roll dough to 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Roll up, starting with long side; seal seam. Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly with palm of hand.
Make large depression in center with fingers.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spoon 1 tablespoon preserves into center of each.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: squirrel stew
directions: Put squirrels in large pot; cover with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, onion and celery.
Cook 1 to 2 hours.
Remove squirrel.
Strain broth; discard onion and celery.
Put broth back in pan; add bay leaf and 2 teaspoons salt.
Add all other ingredients.
Remove squirrel meat from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Add to stew.
Cook 2 hours.
(Remove bay leaf before serving.)

title: aunt bessie's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand.
Mix sugars, oil and eggs.
Add oatmeal mixture and then add flour, cinnamon and salt.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: golden bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Should be moist and chewy.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, melted butter and sugar together. Press in bottom of 8.5 x 11 casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Cream the cream cheese; add powdered sugar.
Mix well and fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Spread over crust.	Mix jello and 1 cup boiling water.
Add strawberries and pour over second layer.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: mary lester's prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour cake mixture into pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until done.

title: party mix
directions: Mix together and cook in 200° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Slowly blend in milk; add lime juice and mix.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until foamy.
Continue beating, adding sugar slowly until egg whites peak.
Fold 6 tablespoons meringue into the filling mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with remaining meringue and bake in slow oven (330°) until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Vegetables may be cooked before adding to chicken and stock. Cook all ingredients, stirring continually to prevent scorching.

title: chicken bake
directions: Layer hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chicken. Mix soup, onion, garlic powder and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
This is a low-fat recipe.

title: mini cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each one. Spoon into 1 1/4-inch mini muffin pans, filling almost full.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
When cool, cover and refrigerate.
Lasts up to 5 days.
When served, top as desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour and baking soda.
In a large bowl, beat until fluffy: butter, sugars, vanilla, pudding and eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips; add small amount of milk of mixture seems dry.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: basil and chickpeas dip
directions: Tastes like a combination of pesto and hummus.
It will keep its fresh flavor for several days.
Add salt just before serving.

title: slaw
directions: Dice onion, pepper and carrots.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar. Shake well in a jar and pour over cabbage mixture.
Will keep more than 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: super salad
directions: Crush uncooked noodles. Add cabbage, sunflower seeds, almonds and green onion tops.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning packet that comes with the noodles. Add to vegetable mixture. Toss well and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Mix flour with butter and chopped nuts.
Put in bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 or more.

title: peter's pot
directions: Drain seafood.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole. Cover and bake in a moderate 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and peppers in a large bowl. Sprinkle with a quarter cup canning salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture onto a small serving plate. Top with nuts.
Serve with apples.
Yields 6 servings.

title: creamed onions
directions: In double boiler, melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly until smooth.
Continue stirring while sauce is thickening, add 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.

title: carrot sour salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Drain carrots; mix all other items and then add carrots. Better if made a day before using.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine pineapple, apples, pear, banana and strawberries in bowl.
In another bowl, mix maple syrup and apple juice.
Mix maple syrup mixture into the apple mixture.
Toss lightly to moisten all fruit pieces.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes in refrigerator.

title: english trifle
directions: Don't use instant jello and pudding.

title: chicken casserole and rice consomme
directions: Place on greased pan
and cover with dried beef.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup (undiluted).
Place strips of bacon on top. Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and oil.
Add flour; mix and roll out.
Cut.
Put in greased pan and let rise about 45 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: thalhimers' richmond room popover
directions: *Chef Danny said the only baking powder that's successful in this recipe is Rumford.

title: glen's grilled onion
directions: Peel onion and core out center.
Rub the onion inside and out with vegetable oil, corn oil or olive oil.
Fill the cavity of the onion with Season-All, lemon pepper, barbecue sauce and butter. Wrap in Reynolds Wrap and place on grill for about 30 minutes.

title: lunch box chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Stir in water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; mix completely.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: fruit pizza
directions: A dessert everyone rushes to get before it disappears!

title: chocolate mocha cake
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: crab salad(15 servings)
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Butter each slice.
Cut bread into small cubes into large bowl.
Add onion and eggs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add crabmeat, shrimp, celery and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Cover.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Serve and enjoy. Delicious!

title: spanish steak
directions: Put steak in casserole and add water; bake in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour, basting every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with salt and pepper and cover with a layer of sliced onions and sprinkle with salt.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cover with layer of tomatoes (the solid meats of 1 can of tomatoes will serve).
Bake again 15 minutes.

Remove from oven; sprinkle cheese over the top and place in the oven until the cheese is melted. There will be a thick gravy deliciously flavored with onions and tomatoes and the steak will be very tender.

title: sunny silver pie
directions: Soak gelatine in 1/3 cup water.
Beat egg yolks until light yellow color; add 1/3 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Cook in top of double boiler until light and fluffy.
Add gelatin and remove from heat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/3 cup of sugar and add to cooked mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate. Cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, pour into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: nothing cake
directions: In an ungreased pan, sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. Make three holes in mixture.
In hole #1 put oil.
In hold #2 put vinegar.
In hole #3 put vanilla.
Pour water over all; stir with fork and mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chicken and dumplings
directions: In Dutch oven, heat to boiling cream of chicken soup, 2 cans of water and salt and pepper to taste.
Tear biscuits into small pieces and place in soup mixture.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat and simmer for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peaches and cream salad
directions: Drain fruit well in a bowl. In a separate bowl mix package if instant pudding with 2 cups of milk and fold in small container of sour cream. Fold in the fruit. Serve same day.

title: oreo dessert
directions: In saucepan, combine chocolate, milk, 1/4 cup butter, sugar and salt.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: best cake doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar till light, add milk and cooled shortening. Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture and mix well.
Chill dough.
On lightly floured board roll 3/8 inch thick and cut.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Fry in fat.

title: georgia peach pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 3 tablespoons syrup.
Cut peaches in small pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Combine cornstarch and 2 to 3 tablespoons sugar.
Add 3 tablespoons reserved peach syrup.
Add remaining sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Stir in melted butter and vanilla.
Pour over peaches and stir until peaches are coated.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, chopped onion and salt together.
Drain. Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Mix hamburger and egg noodles with other ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Before you put in oven, sprinkle with cracker crumbs.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
After baking, melt 4 to 5 slices of cheese on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and taco seasoning, then cool. Don't mix all together until time to serve! Will get soggy if sets too long!

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, buttermilk and eggs.
Add softened butter; beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a well-greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix together the flour, salt, spices and baking powder; set aside.
Add water to raisins and boil briskly 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Stir in soda.
Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well after each addition.
Mix in dry ingredients and add walnuts.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven.

title: apple pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon apple filling into 8 to 10 lightly greased custard cups.
In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Spoon equal portions over apple filling.
Place cups on a 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken rellenos
directions: Debone chicken.
Rub with butter inside and out.
Mix and blend thoroughly ground pork, pork sausage, raisins, grated cheese and 2 eggs.
Stuff chicken and arrange the sweet pickles, sausage and hard-boiled eggs on each side.
Sew up the opening and wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Unwrap foil without removing chicken from foil.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Baste with butter. Cool and serve with sweet potatoes and fried bananas.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, milk, oatmeal, egg, onion, salt, pepper and chili powder together.
Make into walnut-size balls and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: If using self-rising flour, omit the salt and baking powder.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook the onion. Mix ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: bits of brickle coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, butter and sugars.
Take out 1/2 cup of mixture. To the rest, add buttermilk, soda, egg and vanilla.
Blend well. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: new mexican green chili
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add the chilies and jalapenos and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon-lime pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix cream cheese into hot gelatin mixture.
(Use a blender if desired.)
Refrigerate until slightly congealed.
Beat heavy cream with pineapple until smooth.
It will not be stiff.
Stir cream mixture into gelatin mixture, mixing well.
Pour immediately into a lightly oiled mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Spray 9-inch pie pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle with crumbs. In blender or food processor, blend yogurt, egg, sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add cream cheese; blend until smooth. Pour into larger microwavable bowl. Microwave on High (100%), whisking 3 times, 8 to 10 minutes or until consistency of chilled pudding. Remove; stir until smooth. Pour into pie plate. Cover and chill 1 hour. Top with Pineapple Topping.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare batter for cake.
Place half of batter in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt butter, evaporated milk and caramels together.
Pour over baked cake. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining cake batter over top.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Defrost coconut.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in coconut. Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan and bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: hot grape punch
directions: Heat grape juice in a saucepan.
Add sugar and simmer until dissolved.
Stir in lemon juice and cloves.
Simmer 2 minutes longer.
Add the apple.
Pour into glasses.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: shrimp toasts
directions: Grind together the first 3 ingredients or grate in blender. Press down lightly with rubber spatula until grated, then turn onto blend and add next 4 ingredients.
Remove crusts from white bread and spread mixture on one side of bread.
Sprinkle flavored bread crumbs on top.
Fry on both sides until brown with a little oil.
Drain on toweling.
Cut in fourths on the diagonal and serve or freeze.
If frozen, put in oven at 350° for 20 minutes before serving.
Makes a bunch!

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery.
Add rest of ingredients, crumbling bacon into mixture.
Bake in oven on low heat for a few hours or simmer on top of stove.

title: chicken lagoon
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients except chicken and cheese.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with aluminum foil and spread mixture evenly into pan.
Press chicken breasts into mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes; less if breasts are boneless.

title: oatmeal pancakes(yields 4 servings)
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add rolled oats.
Combine egg, oil, molasses, water and milk.
Add to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Cook like pancakes.
Enjoy!

title: gazpacho
directions: In blender, blend the tomatoes, cucumber, onion and green pepper.
Add the juice, vinegar, olive oil and Tabasco sauce. Chill before serving.
Rub bowl with garlic and croutons browned in oil with garlic.
Or serve with dollops of sour cream.

title: chinese hot dish
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients and place in casserole. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° and add 1 can bean sprouts. Bake for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: poor man's lasagna
directions: Boil noodles.
Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with noodles, layer of sauce, layer of hamburger meat and layer of cheese.
Repeat all layers again.
Add extra cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Heat and serve.
(Pretty tasty cold, too!)

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in next three ingredients.
Spread thin layer of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over layer.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes and then at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on.
Peel and dice after cooking. Add other ingredients.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in buttered casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Divide into 2 layers.
Add a cup of ground nuts to 1 part. Add 1 teaspoon of cloves, spices, cinnamon and 1 pound seedless raisins to the other part and bake in layers.

title: dad's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, eggs, salt and spices.
Add milk very slowly mixing well after each addition, keeping mixture smooth. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 (10-inch) or 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: peanut coconut cookies
directions: Sift together dry
ingredients.
Stir
in
sugars;
add margarine, egg and vanilla	and
stir until well mixed.
Blend in peanuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Combine and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon salt.
Let stand one hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Pour vinegar mixture over cabbage. Pack in boxes and freeze.
Can be frozen up to 3 months.

title: lucy's tomato soup
directions: Mix milk, flour, sugar and salt together until smooth.
Pour tomatoes into saucepan and add mixture.
Bring to a gentle boil, being careful not to scorch milk.
Use black pepper to taste.
(If purchased can tomatoes are used, use large can and crush.)
Serve with a pat of butter.

title: beef ole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning, tomato paste and water.
Stir to mix.
Simmer 20 minutes.
To serve, spoon 3/4 cup of meat mixture over 1 cup corn chips.
Top this with any or all of the following: shredded lettuce, grated cheese, chopped tomato, chopped green onions, sliced avocado and sour cream.
Serves 5.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Add 1 liter ginger ale at serving time.

title: mexican corn bread souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine corn, eggs, oil and milk.
Mix dry ingredients and blend well with wet mixture.
Pour half the batter into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Spread the chilies on top and sprinkle with half the cheese.
Pour remaining batter over and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: make ahead meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add the crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Add beef and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls; makes about 12 dozen.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend together. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: the mayors salad
directions: Bring soup and water to boil, stirring constantly.
Add dry jello mix, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat until smooth and well mixed.
Fold in celery, green peppers and onions.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and chill 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: no cholesterol pineapple cream pie
directions: Stir fat-free sour cream to smooth.
Mix together vanilla pudding (dry) and pineapple.
Add the sour cream and fold in until smooth and free of lumps.
Put into crust and chill.
There is no sugar, no fat in the filling of pie and only an infinitesimal amount in pie crust.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and Crisco.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for top.
Add to crumb mixture, buttermilk with baking soda (1 teaspoon), dissolved in milk.
Combine King syrup, hot water, granulated sugar and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda. Mix all together and pour into 3 unbaked pie crusts.
Sprinkle reserved cup of crumbs over pies.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake another 30 minutes or until done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: ham ball
directions: Soften both cheese and ham.
Roll into a ball.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll in parsley.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat to a boil, stirring almost constantly.
When boiling, put on very low heat and cover for a few minutes.
Place in casserole; top with a can of French fried onions.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Great for a quick, easy supper using leftover chicken or turkey.

title: carrot souffle(tastes like sweet potato souffle)
directions: Cook carrots until tender in boiling, salted water.
Drain. Blend carrots and margarine in electric blender until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish or souffle dish and spoon mixture into it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: linda's big hot dish
directions: Brown the ground beef and chopped onions.
Use less onions, if you wish. Drain off all fat.
Put in a large roaster and add peas and juice, corn and juice and celery, chopped with leaves and all. Add all else except the macaroni.
This should be cooked according to directions and then added. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Cut stalk off mushrooms.
Clean out caps.
Wash thoroughly and dice finely.
Melt garlic, butter and stalk.
Cook 10 minutes. Add crumbs and cheese; heat.

title: relyenong ta long(eggplant omelette, filipino style)
directions: Broil eggplant, skin it and put aside.
Heat pan with cooking oil with slow heat; brown garlic.
Stir onion until translucent and mix meat until brown.
Season with soy sauce and dash of pepper. Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Take eggplant and part in the middle; stuff with the cooked ingredients and pour with the scrambled eggplant.
Fry in a large pan.

title: asparagus hot dish
directions: For white sauce, cook flour butter, salt and milk.
Layer asparagus and eggs in casserole.
Pour white sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peek-a-boo drop cookies
directions: Simmer ingredients until thick.

title: cheesy stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash and boil in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes. Drain and cool slightly.
Remove and discard stems.
Cut in half lengthwise and remove pulp and keep shells.
Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp; drain well, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender; stir in bacon, crumbs and pulp.
Put mixture into shells and top with cheese.
Broil for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Combine shortening, butter and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add pecans.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: bird's nest cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on box.
When cooked, add dry cake mix and stir well.
(Do not use mixer.)
Pour into baking dish.
Top with butterscotch chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan, the bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: christmas filbert cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts and fruits with spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: oven roasted veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until veggies are coated.
Empty into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring once, 20 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over it.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: lemon rosemary chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.
Pour over chicken breasts and marinade for several hours or overnight. Grill or broil chicken breasts.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix and pour in loaf pan or large Corning Ware.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with mushroom soup before warming to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, Karo, salt, oleo and vinegar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(2 loaves)
directions: Sift flour in large bowl.
Beat eggs and rest of ingredients to flour mixture; mix well, making sure all zucchini and flour is mixed well into batter.
Scrape bowl often and keep mixing for several minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool in pan on wire rack and store in plastic or in freezer paper and freeze.
This makes 2 loaves.

title: dirt pie or cake
directions: You will need 1 planter and 1 set of fake flowers.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening and molasses.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough rolls easier if refrigerated for several hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Delicious!

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet. Add vegetables and cook until tender. Add broth, rice and seasonings. Mix well. Put in greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite-size pieces.
Cut cauliflower in buds. Add English peas.
Toss; sprinkle onion and bite-size bacon on top.
Spread Good Seasons on top; spread mayonnaise over all. Refrigerate overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and sugar together. Add pumpkin; mix. Put in flour, cinnamon, soda, vanilla, baking powder and salt; mix. Add chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Sprinkle cabbage and onions with salt and pepper.
Bring sugar, celery seed, mustard and vinegar to a boil and boil for one minute. Add salad oil.
Put cabbage in a large bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over cabbage-onion mixture.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before using.
Slaw will stay crisp for a week. This slaw is good with barbecue.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a saucepan combine corn syrup, water, and salt.
Cook over medium heat to 300° or "crack" on candy thermometer.
Stir in butter, baking soda, and vanilla.
Next pour in peanuts and remove from heat.
Pour onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam and spread thin with spatula.
Cool and break in small pieces.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk very slowly until thick to make a paste. Cool.
Add butter, Crisco, sugar, salt and vanilla to paste.
Beat with mixer until thick and creamy.
(Don't underbeat.)
Add crushed, drained pineapple or chopped maraschino cherries.
(A nice party cake.)

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in bowl and mix well.
In another bowl, pour a small amount of confectioners sugar.
Drop cake mix mixture by spoonfuls into confectioners sugar.
Roll into balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 9 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: surprise sauces to simmer with
directions: Combine ingredients in blender and puree.
Pour into saucepan and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over meatballs, steak, etc. Simmer for 1 to 2 hours slowly.

title: fish parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Stir well.
Dip fish fillets in butter and roll in bread crumbs mixture.
Arrange in greased baking dish and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Serve with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: low-fat pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and put in refrigerator to chill.
A dieter's delight!

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until done.
Drain well and let cool.
Mash egg yolks well and put in mustard, sugar and pickle juice.
Mix well.
Put mayonnaise in and stir well.
Then chop egg whites and add to other chopped food.
Add all this to sauce and mix well.
Add to potatoes when cool.
Mix together well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put dough on well flour surface and knead until it is in a good ball.
Then pat dough into a 1/4 thickness and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Put on a greased baking sheet and bake at 450 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: company breakfast(this can be made the day before)
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt; layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish; pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn-yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
When rice is done, add margarine, corn with liquid and cream of chicken soup. Mix and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake until done (about 20 minutes).
Do not cover dish.
When done, spread cheese over top and return to oven for cheese to melt.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: california pineapple cake
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add pineapple with juice, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda, in saucepan.
Cook until syrup turns lightly brown (about 15 minutes).
Remove from fire. Add soda.
Stir and pour onto well buttered surface.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Beat together butter, egg, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and stir well.
Stir in chips. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets 2-inches apart.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chili in bread boats
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, stir ground beef over high heat until crumbly, about 5 minutes.
Add onion and garlic; stir until onion is limp, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and stir in chili powder, cumin and allspice.
Stir until spices are very fragrant, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, green chilies and beans.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thick and beans are hot, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
(If made ahead, cool, cover and chill until the next day.
Reheat to use.) Slice through each roll, about 1/2 inch from top.
Lift off cut portion and hollow out insides of base to make a shell 1/4 inch thick then pull soft bread from top to make lid about 1/4 inch thick; reserve scraps for another use.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Place in a 6-quart casserole. Layer potatoes, onion, pepper, celery salt and pepper.
Then pour tomato juice and water into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 2 hours until potatoes are fork-tender.
Remove lid last 1/2 hour to reduce liquid.
This will cook faster if ingredients are stirred before cooking.

title: rotini salad
directions: Make dressing with oil, vinegar, soy sauce and lemon juice. Toss in vegetables.
Boil Creamettes according to package directions. Combine gently.

title: amy's birthday cake
directions: Bake cake as per package and cool.
Slice cake into four layers.
Place first layer into pan and press down.
Arrange strawberries on cake layer; sprinkle with dry strawberry jello. Spread 1/3 of a half gallon softened ice cream on top of fruit and jello.
Place next layer of cake in pan and press.
Top with mandarin oranges (drained) on top of cake and sprinkle with dry orange jello.
Spread 1/3 of a half gallon softened ice cream on top of fruit and jello.
Place next layer of cake in pan and press.
Top with blueberries (drained) on top of cake and sprinkle with dry lemon jello.
Spread 1/3 of a half gallon softened ice cream on top of fruit and jello.
Place last layer of cake in pan and press.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie shee. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Lightly coat biscuits with butter as soon as you take them out of the oven.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Pack into jars; seal.
Label to read:
Use 2 to 3 level tablespoons mix for a 6 ounce cup boiling water.

title: double chocolate gooey butter cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 13 by 9 inch baking pan. In a large bowl, combine the cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick melted butter and stir until well blended. Pat mixture into prepared pan and set aside.

In a stand mixer, or with a hand mixer, beat the cream cheese until smooth. Add the remaining 2 eggs, and the cocoa powder. Lower the speed of the mixer and add the powdered sugar. Continue beating until ingredients are well mixed. Slowly add the remaining 1 stick of melted butter and the vanilla, continuing to beat the mixture until smooth. Stir in nuts with a rubber spatula. Spread filling over cake mixture in pan. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes. Be careful not to overcook the cake; the center should still be a little gooey when finished baking. let cake partially cool on a wire rack before cutting into pieces.

title: tortellini with tomato and parmesan mushroom sauce
directions: To make tomato sauce, melt 1 tablespoon of the butter in medium saucepan.
Cook onion and garlic until tender.
Add oil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle pecans and raisins in pan to cover bottom.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Cut 2 loaves of frozen bread into 6 pieces (each loaf).
Place on top of pecans and raisins.
Sprinkle bread with cinnamon.
Mix pudding mix, brown sugar, butter and milk.
Pour over top of bread.
Preheat oven to 200° and turn off.
Place pan in oven over pan of warm water for 1 1/2 hours or until raised.
Remove from oven.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove and brush with butter. Turn pan over and let stand until cool.
Great warmed in microwave for 30 seconds for each roll.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, strawberries and oil and add to sifted ingredients.
Add pecans.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake for about 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then cool on wire rack.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in a buttered baking dish.	Drizzle top with 1/2
cup
melted
butter.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve either hot or cold.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Roast the prime rib of beef according to cooking instructions. While meat cooks, sift together flour and salt.
Stir in milk, beating vigorously until smooth.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each egg.
Chill 2 hours.
Half an hour before roast is done, put 1/4 cup of beef drippings in a roasting pan.
Set in the oven until sizzling hot.
Cook pudding 15 minutes in oven at 350° or until golden and crisp at edges.
Add some dripping and use the rest for gravy.

title: bunket
directions: Paste:
Beat eggs well with electric mixer.
Add sugar slowly and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add paste.
Cut up fine.
Set in the refrigerator to chill overnight.
Cover tight.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello and stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries immediately and mix gently.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Put 1/2 of mixture into lightly oiled 9-inch pan.
Chill slightly.
Fold sour cream into remaining mixture and pour carefully into chilled mixture.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: In a large pot, combine all of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer about 10 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.
Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: moist banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine soda, buttermilk and vanilla in a small bowl.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Cut shortening into dry mixture.
Mix in milk and egg.
Keeps good in refrigerator.
Chill overnight, if possible.
It is much easier to work with then.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Slice apples; place in a large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples and toss well. Spoon into unbaked pie shell and drizzle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup flour and stick margarine, then sprinkle over apples.
Slide pie into brown paper bag.
Fold open end twice and fasten with paper clip.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 1 hour.

title: clam dip
directions: Whip together all the ingredients.
Put into a small, ovenproof serving bowl.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and serve with crackers.

title: pita pizza
directions: Slice pita bread in half.
Spread pizza sauce.
Layer with toppings and spread Mozzarella cheese on top.
Cook in toaster oven 5 minutes at 425°.

title: raspberry-pineapple jello mold
directions: Line pan with mayonnaise. In large bowl dissolve jello with hot water. Add carrots, celery, nuts and pineapple.
Mix well. Put into mold. refrigerate until set.

title: tuna fish cocktail balls
directions: Crush cereal finely.
Combine half of the cereal with the milk. Add remaining ingredients, except reserved cereal.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in remaining crushed cereal.
Bake (425°) on greased baking sheets for 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: iowa burgers
directions: Mix well.
Shape into patties and broil until done.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Boil celery until soft and drain.
Combine meat, celery, soups and 1/2 can of noodles. Place in greased casserole.
Top with the remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle orange Jell-O over cottage cheese and Cool Whip; mix together and add fruit.

title: maple pecan corn bread
directions: In a bowl combine well the flour, cornmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices; mix about 1/2 cup with nuts and fruit.
Cream shortening until soft and smooth, gradually adding sugar, creaming until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce, beating well after each addition.
Beat in fruit-nut mixture.
Turn into greased pans in moderately slow oven (325°), baking about 1 hour. Nuts and dates may be omitted, if desired.
Yield: 2 small loaves (6 x 3-inches) or 1 large loaf (11 x 3 x 3-inches).

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a 9 1/2-inch ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta cobb salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Chop green onion (tips only) and dried beets into small pieces.
In medium bowl, mix the ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts. Place in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: relish(makes 4 pints)
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil, stir until sugar dissolves.
Stir in vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put in jars, hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix wet ingredients thoroughly, then add dry ingredients until blended.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 35 minutes.

title: potato buds bake(great for make ahead; everyone likes; easy)
directions: Make recipe on instant Potato Buds box except short water by 1/4 cup for 12.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, Miracle Whip, egg and finely chopped onions and tops.
With mixer, mix until smooth. Spray casserole with Pam.
Fill with mixture; don't cover.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or longer if made ahead and refrigerated.

title: punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crusts.
Store in refrigerator.
Allow 24 hours to set.
Yields 2 pies.

title: turkey broccoli casserole(day after christmas main dish)
directions: In a large casserole, combine 1/2 cup of onion rings and all other ingredients, keeping enough grated cheese and pimento to decorate top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir; top with remaining onions, cheese and pimento and bake 5 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: tartar sauce
directions: To 1 cup mayonnaise, add all of the ingredients and blend well.
Chill.
Good served with fried fish.

title: baked turkey
directions: Put in pan with tight lid.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 1 hour; turn oven off.
Do not open oven door.
Let set overnight.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Heat oil.
Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides.
Add water to reserved pineapple juice to make 3/4 cup.

title: chess pie
directions: Add all ingredients together and pour an unbaked shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: herb dumpling chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in large Dutch oven with 1 whole carrot, 1 onion, celery stalk and seasonings.
Cover with hot water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: pepper steak sandwiches
directions: In a large skillet, saute the onion and peppers in 3 Tbsp. of mayonnaise until crisp and tender. Remove vegetables and keep warm. Reduce heat. Add the Italian dressing, roast beef and the remaining mayonnaise to the skillet.
Cook and stir until heated through, about 5 minutes. Place beef and vegetables on rolls; top with mozzarella cheese.

title: chow chow
directions: *Use as much as you like.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Bake in 2 cake pans (lightly greased) for 20 minutes in 300° oven.

title: hot stewed tomatoes
directions: To a quart of canned tomatoes, add extra salt, if needed, a dash of pepper, sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Heat to boiling point. Serve in bowls.

title: smokey potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Meanwhile, halve 3 sausage links crosswise and slice remaining sausage links.
Prepare potatoes according to package directions, except omit butter.
Stir in celery and sliced sausage.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Stir and place halved links on top. Bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: chicken delight
directions: Bake chicken at 350° until done.
Let cool, then debone.
Add hot sauce, catsup, lemon juice, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and onion.
Mix together and pour over chicken.
Add carrots and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have eggs at room temperature.
Measure sifted flour; add 1/2 cup sugar and sift 4 times.
Combine egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar in large bowl; beat until moist peaks form.
Add remaining sugar in 4 additions, beating slightly after each addition.
Fold in flour mixture in 4 additions; turn bowl often.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool upside down.

title: fish batter
directions: Open can of beer in morning and let stand about 3 hours.
Beat flour, salt, baking powder and egg yolks into beer.
Let stand 1 hour or more.
Just before using, beat egg whites very stiff and fold into batter.
Dip fish and fry.

title: poor man's soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 2 hours.

title: easy barbecue pork chops
directions: Arrange chops in single layer in baking pan.
Lightly salt and pepper each chop.
On each chop, place one slice of onion, one tablespoon of ketchup, one tablespoon brown sugar and a few drops of lemon juice.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn chops and bake 20 minutes longer.
Baste each chop frequently for another 20 minutes (at intervals), coating each chop.
Sauce will thicken during basting time.
Serve with cooked white rice.

title: quick cheaters rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until batter is smooth. Pour into a greased 12 muffin tin.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rolled molasses cookies
directions: Mix hot tea and soda until fizzes, then cool.
Beat eggs and sugar; add molasses and cooled shortening.
Stir in cooled tea mixture.
Stir in dry ingredients to form stiff dough.
Let set 1 hour or more.
Roll out on floured board; cut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: great apple crisp
directions: Mix apples with other ingredients and chill for 1-1/2 hours.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Put dates, water and butter in a bowl.
In second bowl, put eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Place dry ingredients in third bowl.
Add egg mixture to date mixture, then add flour mixture.
Last add chopped nuts.
Put batter into 4 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies - "jewels"
directions: Use red or green candied cherry halves or pecan halves for top of cookie.
Combine salt with soda and flour; set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately.
Add nuts, fruit and raisins.
Chill dough for several hours.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with fruit or pecan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt together the oleo and caramels.
Add condensed milk and mix well.
Pour mixture over baked cake.
Pour rest of cake mix over top of caramel mixture and top with pecans and chocolate bits.
May sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, pecans and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9-inch square pan, stirring often.
Let cool.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Heat 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 cup water to boiling.
Add vegetable, bring to a boil and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix vegetable, onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: swiss asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and use the liquid to thin down the cream of asparagus soup to the consistency of thick gravy.
Place cut asparagus, eggs, cheese, pepper and 1/2 of the onions in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over all and mix gently.
Cover with remaining onions.
Heat in oven until hot and bubbly.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Cream together.
Add corn flakes and mix sparingly.
Put into buttered cake pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain well.
Cool.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix well. Add potatoes and eggs.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: tuna layer salad
directions: Prepare lime gelatin.
Pour into large pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Sprinkle unflavored gelatin over surface of cold water and let soften several minutes.
Beat egg yolk with salt, mustard and paprika in top of double boiler.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Cook over hot water until mixture thickens (5 or 7 minutes), stirring constantly.
Add softened gelatin to hot mixture and stir until dissolved.
Chill mixture until it begins to set.
Stir in tuna, green pepper and celery.
Fold in mayonnaise, then the egg whites beaten until stiff, but not dry.
Spoon mixture gently over lime gelatin.
Chill until tuna mixture is set (2 or 3 hours).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick butter.
Put on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill well.
Delicious with roast beef.

title: diabetic cupcakes
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft.
Drain off water.
Mix applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Add soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 dozen cakes.
One cake equals 1 fruit and 1 fat exchange.

title: honey chicken
directions: Prepare Time - 10 minutes

title: german chocolate dump cake
directions: Sprinkle the pecans and coconut over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Combine cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Spoon this mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: butterflied garlic shrimp
directions: Heat butter in large frying pan.
Add shrimp and cook 2 minutes on each side over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and season well. Continue cooking for 1 minute.
Stir in green peppers and diced lemon.
Cook 1 more minute.
Add parsley, paprika, salt and pepper. Mix and serve.

title: cherokee yam cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt into a bowl.
Pour oil and milk into a measuring cup but do not stir.
Add to yams. Blend well.
Add to flour mixture and mix lightly with a fork until mixture holds together.
Turn dough out onto floured board and knead gently until smooth (about 12 kneading strokes).
Roll dough about 1/4-inch thick and cut into rounds with floured biscuit cutter.
Place rounds on a baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot or split when cold and toast.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine corn, red pepper, onion, pickle relish and celery in medium heatproof bowl.
Stir together vinegar, oil, sugar, mustard, mustard seed and celery seed in small saucepan.
Bring to boiling; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over vegetables; stir well. Refrigerate, covered, overnight, stirring occasionally.
Spoon relish into glass jar and tightly cover.
Store in icebox up to one week.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use with bread or veggies.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook broccoli and drain. Cook chicken and cut into pieces. Shred cheese. Layer broccoli first in 13 x 9 x 2 pan, then chicken, then cheese. Mix cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry and spread over cheese layer. Melt butter. Dredge bread crumbs in butter. Put on top of mayonnaise layer. Yields 6 servings.

title: curried chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken gravy mix, curry powder and water in large size (14 x 20-inch) oven cooking bag and place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Season chicken breasts with salt, pepper and paprika; place in single layer in bag.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes, until tender.
Serves 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and the dry pudding.
Add pineapple, pecans and marshmallows.
Blend together and chill.

title: old time molasses cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Stir in ginger and cinnamon; add salt and egg.
Beat until well blended. Stir molasses and buttermilk.
Sift together flour and soda. Combine with batter; beat just enough to incorporate flour.
Pour into greased 10-inch skillet.
Bake in 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serve with lemon butter.

title: dump pound cake
directions: Beat at high speed for 20 minutes.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Don't preheat oven.
Don't butter or flour pan.)
Can be used to make cupcakes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans on bottom.
Place frozen rolls on pecans.
Mix margarine, sugar, pudding, milk and cinnamon.
Pour mixture over top of rolls.
Set out overnight (8 hours minimum) for dough to rise.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Turn over onto serving plate.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers in cold water.
Slice and pack in jars.
Put 1/4 teaspoon powdered alum to 1 quart.
Add 2 teaspoons dill seed and 1 garlic bulb.
Mix vinegar, water and salt; bring to a boil.
Pour in jars and seal.
Let sit for 6 weeks.

title: jack's soup
directions: Brown meat in large stock pot. Add vegetables, onion, celery and carrots to taste, tomatoes and tomato sauce, potatoes (cubed), liquids and spices.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Rinse frozen broccoli under cold water to separate; drain. Mix hamburg, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and oregano.
Pat mixture into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle on foil.
Arrange broccoli on hamburg to within 1/2-inch from edges. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Arrange ham on broccoli.
Roll up rectangle at 10-inch side and using foil to lift press edges and ends to seal.
Place in shallow pan and bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Overlap cheese on top and bake 1 minute.
(Center of meat loaf may be slightly pink due to ham.)

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples to fill pie pan 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
In small bowl combine the next 5 ingredients and nuts (optional).
Pour over apples and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until crust is golden brown.
Rhubarb, berries and other fresh fruit can be substituted for the apples.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine and chill until ready to serve.
Add 1 bottle of ginger ale.
Serves 40 punch cups.

title: sour cabbage
directions: Chop onion and apple fine.
Put in frying pan with shortening for 10 minutes.
Add cabbage which has been shredded.
Add water a little at a time to keep mixture steaming.
Cook for 20 minutes. When it is tender, add sugar and vinegar.
Before serving, add salt, pepper and butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone and chop.
Put in baking dish.
Mix broth, milk and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Cook celery and onions in small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Add egg and stuffing mix.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage-mushroom breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Sprinkle sausage over croutons.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mushroom and mustard; mix well and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain all fat and add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix cheese and sausage, then add Bisquick mix in 3 equal parts.
Dough will be stiff.
Knead several minutes and set aside. Slit and seed jalapeno peppers.
Stuff each pepper with a piece of cheese and pinch back together.
Pinch off a piece of sausage mixture and pat into flat pancake.
Place the pepper in the middle and wrap around dough until covered.
Roll back and forth in hands to form egg shape.
Roll each egg in shake and bake.
Eggs can be baked now or frozen.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs and sugar together.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stays fresh for days.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put meat in 12 hours before cooking time.
Good for roasts, steaks, kabobs or most any meat.

title: chicken salad
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add mayonnaise, parsley, garlic, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Cook chicken breasts, skin and debone and then chop.
Combine mayonnaise mixture with chicken, toasted almonds and white grapes.
Refrigerate and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: excellent salsa
directions: Beat egg yolks in top of double boiler with wire whisk until smooth but not fluffy. Add melted butter, lemon juice, hot water and salt. Place over hot water and beat until sauce begins to thicken, about 5 minutes.
Add parsley and tarragon. Add cold water and beat if mixture begins to separate. Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In a sauce pan, mix brown sugar, egg yolks and flour; add water and salt, cook over medium heat stirring frequently.	After mixture has thickened, remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Pour mixture in pie shell and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken bake
directions: Wrap 1 strip of bacon around each piece of chicken. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken in casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika and bake for 3 hours, uncovered, at 275°.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat the egg and add the with vinegar to make one cup very cold water. Makes one cup liquid.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers; cream butter and sugar together.
Add orange juice, wafers and pecans.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all together for 3 minutes.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Add enough ice to cold water to measure 1 cup.
Add to gelatin. Stir until ice is melted.

title: apricot pull aparts
directions: Cut bread dough (thawed) in half lengthwise, then cut into 8 pieces crosswise (16 pieces total).
Flatten pieces of dough with your fingers, stretching slightly to form 4-inch circles.
Using 1 can of apricot or prune pastry filling, spoon 1 tablespoon of filling in center of each circle.
Bring edges of dough together; pinch to seal.
Dip in 3 tablespoons of melted margarine, then in 1/3 cup sugar.
Place, seam side down, in 2 layers in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover; let rise until almost double.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done, covering with foil during the last 10 minutes of baking.
Remove from the pan.
Invert onto a serving platter.
Serve warm.

title: quiche
directions: Line bottom of pie pan with asparagus. Beat rest of ingredients and pour over asparagus.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in dish and freeze. Serve frozen or slightly thawed (like ice cream).
Lasts up to 6 months.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted milk chocolate bits over mixture in pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: vegie dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and dissolved beef bouillon with mixer. Once blended, add jar of mayonnaise; blend until creamy.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: dressing
directions: Bring celery and chicken broth to a boil and cook until celery is partly tender. Tear bread into cubes and pour celery and onion mixture over bread.
Add sage, salt, pepper and butter to mixture. Pour mixture into buttered baking pan. Bake at 350° until brown around the edges.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed; mix well.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.
Yield: 16.

title: baked shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Bring broccoli and water to a full boil on medium high heat. Add rice, stir, then cover and remove from heat and let stand for 4-5 minutes.
Stir in Velveeta Cheese.
Cover and let stand 4-5 minutes longer until the cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute okra, onion and green pepper in margarine or bacon fat over low heat.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring as little as possible.

title: ranch crackers
directions: Dissolve dressing mix and garlic powder in oil.
Dump crackers into large mixing bowl that can be sealed for storage.
Pour oil mixture over crackers; gently stir to thoroughly coat crackers. Seal and store overnight.
Crackers will absorb oil and seasonings overnight and then are ready to enjoy.
Keeps well for several weeks.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken or hen until tender.
Remove chicken from broth. Sift one sifter of plain flour.
Make hole in center and pour in 1 cup broth.
Make up as you do biscuits.
Make dough real stiff. Pinch off piece of dough about the size of a small fist.
Place dough on floured surface.
Roll dough very thin.
Cut into strips with knife.
Pick up strips and stretch and break into pieces about 3 inches long.
Drop into boiling broth.
Debone chicken and add to dumplings, lower heat and boil until dumplings are done.

title: scottsdale potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 7 x 10-inch ovenproof glass baking dish.
In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients; season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to baking dish.
Mix cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted butter and spread on top of potato mixture. Bake for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugar, one cup at a time, creaming thoroughly after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour; measure.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately into creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Pan may be lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes (great with Caramel Icing).

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in large flat buttered baking dish. Combine soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and pepper.
Mix and pour over potatoes.
Stir corn flakes in melted margarine and spread on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
